118struct ImBitVector; // Store 1-bit per value
119struct ImRect; // An axis-aligned rectangle (2 points)
120struct ImDrawDataBuilder; // Helper to build a ImDrawData instance
121struct ImDrawListSharedData; // Data shared between all ImDrawList instances
122struct ImGuiColorMod; // Stacked color modifier, backup of modified data so we can restore it
123struct ImGuiContext; // Main Dear ImGui context
124struct ImGuiContextHook; // Hook for extensions like ImGuiTestEngine
125struct ImGuiDataVarInfo; // Variable information (e.g. to avoid style variables from an enum)
126struct ImGuiDataTypeInfo; // Type information associated to a ImGuiDataType enum
127struct ImGuiDockContext; // Docking system context
128struct ImGuiDockRequest; // Docking system dock/undock queued request
129struct ImGuiDockNode; // Docking system node (hold a list of Windows OR two child dock nodes)
130struct ImGuiDockNodeSettings; // Storage for a dock node in .ini file (we preserve those even if the associated dock node isn't active during the session)
131struct ImGuiGroupData; // Stacked storage data for BeginGroup()/EndGroup()
132struct ImGuiInputTextState; // Internal state of the currently focused/edited text input box
133struct ImGuiInputTextDeactivateData;// Short term storage to backup text of a deactivating InputText() while another is stealing active id
134struct ImGuiLastItemData; // Status storage for last submitted items
135struct ImGuiLocEntry; // A localization entry.
136struct ImGuiMenuColumns; // Simple column measurement, currently used for MenuItem() only
137struct ImGuiNavItemData; // Result of a gamepad/keyboard directional navigation move query result
138struct ImGuiNavTreeNodeData; // Temporary storage for last TreeNode() being a Left arrow landing candidate.
139struct ImGuiMetricsConfig; // Storage for ShowMetricsWindow() and DebugNodeXXX() functions
140struct ImGuiNextWindowData; // Storage for SetNextWindow** functions
141struct ImGuiNextItemData; // Storage for SetNextItem** functions
142struct ImGuiOldColumnData; // Storage data for a single column for legacy Columns() api
143struct ImGuiOldColumns; // Storage data for a columns set for legacy Columns() api
144struct ImGuiPopupData; // Storage for current popup stack
145struct ImGuiSettingsHandler; // Storage for one type registered in the .ini file
146struct ImGuiStackSizes; // Storage of stack sizes for debugging/asserting
147struct ImGuiStyleMod; // Stacked style modifier, backup of modified data so we can restore it
148struct ImGuiTabBar; // Storage for a tab bar
149struct ImGuiTabItem; // Storage for a tab item (within a tab bar)
150struct ImGuiTable; // Storage for a table
151struct ImGuiTableColumn; // Storage for one column of a table
152struct ImGuiTableInstanceData; // Storage for one instance of a same table
153struct ImGuiTableTempData; // Temporary storage for one table (one per table in the stack), shared between tables.
154struct ImGuiTableSettings; // Storage for a table .ini settings
155struct ImGuiTableColumnsSettings; // Storage for a column .ini settings
156struct ImGuiTypingSelectState; // Storage for GetTypingSelectRequest()
157struct ImGuiTypingSelectRequest; // Storage for GetTypingSelectRequest() (aimed to be public)
158struct ImGuiWindow; // Storage for one window
159struct ImGuiWindowTempData; // Temporary storage for one window (that's the data which in theory we could ditch at the end of the frame, in practice we currently keep it for each window)
160struct ImGuiWindowSettings; // Storage for a window .ini settings (we keep one of those even if the actual window wasn't instanced during this session)

222// Debug Printing Into TTY
223// (since IMGUI_VERSION_NUM >= 18729: IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG was reworked into IMGUI_DEBUG_PRINTF (and removed framecount from it). If you were using a #define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG please rename)
224#ifndef IMGUI_DEBUG_PRINTF
225#ifndef IMGUI_DISABLE_DEFAULT_FORMAT_FUNCTIONS
226#define IMGUI_DEBUG_PRINTF(_FMT,...) printf(_FMT, __VA_ARGS__)
227#else
228#define IMGUI_DEBUG_PRINTF(_FMT,...) ((void)0)
229#endif
230#endif

232// Debug Logging for ShowDebugLogWindow(). This is designed for relatively rare events so please don't spam.
233#ifndef IMGUI_DISABLE_DEBUG_TOOLS
234#define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(...) ImGui::DebugLog(__VA_ARGS__)
235#else
236#define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(...) ((void)0)
237#endif
238#define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_ACTIVEID(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventActiveId) IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)
239#define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_FOCUS(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventFocus) IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)
240#define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_POPUP(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventPopup) IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)
241#define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_NAV(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventNav) IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)
242#define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_SELECTION(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventSelection)IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)
243#define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_CLIPPER(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventClipper) IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)
244#define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_IO(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventIO) IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)
245#define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_DOCKING(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventDocking) IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)
246#define IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG_VIEWPORT(...) do { if (g.DebugLogFlags & ImGuiDebugLogFlags_EventViewport) IMGUI_DEBUG_LOG(__VA_ARGS__); } while (0)

248// Static Asserts

251// "Paranoid" Debug Asserts are meant to only be enabled during specific debugging/work, otherwise would slow down the code too much.
252// We currently don't have many of those so the effect is currently negligible, but onward intent to add more aggressive ones in the code.
253//#define IMGUI_DEBUG_PARANOID
254#ifdef IMGUI_DEBUG_PARANOID
255#define IM_ASSERT_PARANOID(_EXPR) IM_ASSERT(_EXPR)
256#else
257#define IM_ASSERT_PARANOID(_EXPR)
258#endif

260// Error handling
261// Down the line in some frameworks/languages we would like to have a way to redirect those to the programmer and recover from more faults.
262#ifndef IM_ASSERT_USER_ERROR
263#define IM_ASSERT_USER_ERROR(_EXP,_MSG) IM_ASSERT((_EXP) && _MSG) // Recoverable User Error
264#endif

274#define IM_TABSIZE (4)

276#define IM_MEMALIGN(_OFF,_ALIGN) (((_OFF) + ((_ALIGN) - 1)) & ~((_ALIGN) - 1)) // Memory align e.g. IM_ALIGN(0,4)=0, IM_ALIGN(1,4)=4, IM_ALIGN(4,4)=4, IM_ALIGN(5,4)=8
277#define IM_F32_TO_INT8_UNBOUND(_VAL) ((int)((_VAL) * 255.0f + ((_VAL)>=0 ? 0.5f : -0.5f))) // Unsaturated, for display purpose
278#define IM_F32_TO_INT8_SAT(_VAL) ((int)(ImSaturate(_VAL) * 255.0f + 0.5f)) // Saturated, always output 0..255
279#define IM_TRUNC(_VAL) ((float)(int)(_VAL)) // ImTrunc() is not inlined in MSVC debug builds
280#define IM_ROUND(_VAL) ((float)(int)((_VAL) + 0.5f)) //
281#define IM_STRINGIFY_HELPER(_X) #_X
282#define IM_STRINGIFY(_X) IM_STRINGIFY_HELPER(_X) // Preprocessor idiom to stringify e.g. an integer.
283#ifndef IMGUI_DISABLE_OBSOLETE_FUNCTIONS

301// Debug Tools
302// Use 'Metrics/Debugger->Tools->Item Picker' to break into the call-stack of a specific item.
303// This will call IM_DEBUG_BREAK() which you may redefine yourself. See https://github.com/scottt/debugbreak for more reference.
304#ifndef IM_DEBUG_BREAK
305#if defined (_MSC_VER)
306#define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() __debugbreak()
307#elif defined(__clang__)
308#define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() __builtin_debugtrap()
309#elif defined(__GNUC__) && (defined(__i386__) || defined(__x86_64__))
310#define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() __asm__ volatile("int $0x03")
311#elif defined(__GNUC__) && defined(__thumb__)
312#define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() __asm__ volatile(".inst 0xde01")
313#elif defined(__GNUC__) && defined(__arm__) && !defined(__thumb__)
314#define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() __asm__ volatile(".inst 0xe7f001f0");
315#else
316#define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() IM_ASSERT(0) // It is expected that you define IM_DEBUG_BREAK() into something that will break nicely in a debugger!
317#endif
318#endif // #ifndef IM_DEBUG_BREAK

320// Format specifiers, printing 64-bit hasn't been decently standardized...
321// In a real application you should be using PRId64 and PRIu64 from <inttypes.h> (non-windows) and on Windows define them yourself.
322#if defined(_MSC_VER) && !defined(__clang__)
323#define IM_PRId64 "I64d"
324#define IM_PRIu64 "I64u"
325#define IM_PRIX64 "I64X"
326#else
327#define IM_PRId64 "lld"
328#define IM_PRIu64 "llu"
329#define IM_PRIX64 "llX"
330#endif

361// Helpers: Sorting
362#ifndef ImQsort
363static inline void ImQsort(void* base, size_t count, size_t size_of_element, int(IMGUI_CDECL *compare_func)(void const*, void const*)) { if (count > 1) qsort(base, count, size_of_element, compare_func); }
364#endif

368
369// Helpers: Bit manipulation
370static inline bool ImIsPowerOfTwo(int v) { return v != 0 && (v & (v - 1)) == 0; }
371static inline bool ImIsPowerOfTwo(ImU64 v) { return v != 0 && (v & (v - 1)) == 0; }
372static inline int ImUpperPowerOfTwo(int v) { v--; v |= v >> 1; v |= v >> 2; v |= v >> 4; v |= v >> 8; v |= v >> 16; v++; return v; }

387IM_MSVC_RUNTIME_CHECKS_OFF
388static inline char ImToUpper(char c) { return (c >= 'a' && c <= 'z') ? c &= ~32 : c; }
389static inline bool ImCharIsBlankA(char c) { return c == ' ' || c == '\t'; }
390static inline bool ImCharIsBlankW(unsigned int c) { return c == ' ' || c == '\t' || c == 0x3000; }

437// Helpers: Maths
438IM_MSVC_RUNTIME_CHECKS_OFF
439// - Wrapper for standard libs functions. (Note that imgui_demo.cpp does _not_ use them to keep the code easy to copy)
440#ifndef IMGUI_DISABLE_DEFAULT_MATH_FUNCTIONS
441#define ImFabs(X) fabsf(X)
442#define ImSqrt(X) sqrtf(X)
443#define ImFmod(X, Y) fmodf((X), (Y))
444#define ImCos(X) cosf(X)
445#define ImSin(X) sinf(X)
446#define ImAcos(X) acosf(X)
447#define ImAtan2(Y, X) atan2f((Y), (X))
448#define ImAtof(STR) atof(STR)
449#define ImCeil(X) ceilf(X)
450static inline float ImPow(float x, float y) { return powf(x, y); } // DragBehaviorT/SliderBehaviorT uses ImPow with either float/double and need the precision
451static inline double ImPow(double x, double y) { return pow(x, y); }
452static inline float ImLog(float x) { return logf(x); } // DragBehaviorT/SliderBehaviorT uses ImLog with either float/double and need the precision
453static inline double ImLog(double x) { return log(x); }
454static inline int ImAbs(int x) { return x < 0 ? -x : x; }
455static inline float ImAbs(float x) { return fabsf(x); }
456static inline double ImAbs(double x) { return fabs(x); }
457static inline float ImSign(float x) { return (x < 0.0f) ? -1.0f : (x > 0.0f) ? 1.0f : 0.0f; } // Sign operator - returns -1, 0 or 1 based on sign of argument
458static inline double ImSign(double x) { return (x < 0.0) ? -1.0 : (x > 0.0) ? 1.0 : 0.0; }
459#ifdef IMGUI_ENABLE_SSE
460static inline float ImRsqrt(float x) { return _mm_cvtss_f32(_mm_rsqrt_ss(_mm_set_ss(x))); }
461#else
462static inline float ImRsqrt(float x) { return 1.0f / sqrtf(x); }
463#endif
464static inline double ImRsqrt(double x) { return 1.0 / sqrt(x); }
465#endif
466// - ImMin/ImMax/ImClamp/ImLerp/ImSwap are used by widgets which support variety of types: signed/unsigned int/long long float/double
467// (Exceptionally using templates here but we could also redefine them for those types)
468template<typename T> static inline T ImMin(T lhs, T rhs) { return lhs < rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
469template<typename T> static inline T ImMax(T lhs, T rhs) { return lhs >= rhs ? lhs : rhs; }
470template<typename T> static inline T ImClamp(T v, T mn, T mx) { return (v < mn) ? mn : (v > mx) ? mx : v; }
471template<typename T> static inline T ImLerp(T a, T b, float t) { return (T)(a + (b - a) * t); }
472template<typename T> static inline void ImSwap(T& a, T& b) { T tmp = a; a = b; b = tmp; }
473template<typename T> static inline T ImAddClampOverflow(T a, T b, T mn, T mx) { if (b < 0 && (a < mn - b)) return mn; if (b > 0 && (a > mx - b)) return mx; return a + b; }
474template<typename T> static inline T ImSubClampOverflow(T a, T b, T mn, T mx) { if (b > 0 && (a < mn + b)) return mn; if (b < 0 && (a > mx + b)) return mx; return a - b; }
475// - Misc maths helpers
476static inline ImVec2 ImMin(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x < rhs.x ? lhs.x : rhs.x, lhs.y < rhs.y ? lhs.y : rhs.y); }
477static inline ImVec2 ImMax(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x >= rhs.x ? lhs.x : rhs.x, lhs.y >= rhs.y ? lhs.y : rhs.y); }
478static inline ImVec2 ImClamp(const ImVec2& v, const ImVec2& mn, ImVec2 mx) { return ImVec2((v.x < mn.x) ? mn.x : (v.x > mx.x) ? mx.x : v.x, (v.y < mn.y) ? mn.y : (v.y > mx.y) ? mx.y : v.y); }
479static inline ImVec2 ImLerp(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, float t) { return ImVec2(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t); }
480static inline ImVec2 ImLerp(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b, const ImVec2& t) { return ImVec2(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t.x, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t.y); }
481static inline ImVec4 ImLerp(const ImVec4& a, const ImVec4& b, float t) { return ImVec4(a.x + (b.x - a.x) * t, a.y + (b.y - a.y) * t, a.z + (b.z - a.z) * t, a.w + (b.w - a.w) * t); }
482static inline float ImSaturate(float f) { return (f < 0.0f) ? 0.0f : (f > 1.0f) ? 1.0f : f; }
483static inline float ImLengthSqr(const ImVec2& lhs) { return (lhs.x * lhs.x) + (lhs.y * lhs.y); }
484static inline float ImLengthSqr(const ImVec4& lhs) { return (lhs.x * lhs.x) + (lhs.y * lhs.y) + (lhs.z * lhs.z) + (lhs.w * lhs.w); }
485static inline float ImInvLength(const ImVec2& lhs, float fail_value) { float d = (lhs.x * lhs.x) + (lhs.y * lhs.y); if (d > 0.0f) return ImRsqrt(d); return fail_value; }
486static inline float ImTrunc(float f) { return (float)(int)(f); }
487static inline ImVec2 ImTrunc(const ImVec2& v) { return ImVec2((float)(int)(v.x), (float)(int)(v.y)); }
488static inline float ImFloor(float f) { return (float)((f >= 0 || (float)(int)f == f) ? (int)f : (int)f - 1); } // Decent replacement for floorf()
489static inline ImVec2 ImFloor(const ImVec2& v) { return ImVec2(ImFloor(v.x), ImFloor(v.y)); }
490static inline int ImModPositive(int a, int b) { return (a + b) % b; }
491static inline float ImDot(const ImVec2& a, const ImVec2& b) { return a.x * b.x + a.y * b.y; }
492static inline ImVec2 ImRotate(const ImVec2& v, float cos_a, float sin_a) { return ImVec2(v.x * cos_a - v.y * sin_a, v.x * sin_a + v.y * cos_a); }
493static inline float ImLinearSweep(float current, float target, float speed) { if (current < target) return ImMin(current + speed, target); if (current > target) return ImMax(current - speed, target); return current; }
494static inline ImVec2 ImMul(const ImVec2& lhs, const ImVec2& rhs) { return ImVec2(lhs.x * rhs.x, lhs.y * rhs.y); }
495static inline bool ImIsFloatAboveGuaranteedIntegerPrecision(float f) { return f <= -16777216 || f >= 16777216; }
496static inline float ImExponentialMovingAverage(float avg, float sample, int n) { avg -= avg / n; avg += sample / n; return avg; }
497IM_MSVC_RUNTIME_CHECKS_RESTORE

529// Helper: ImRect (2D axis aligned bounding-box)
530// NB: we can't rely on ImVec2 math operators being available here!
531struct IMGUI_API ImRect
532{
533 ImVec2 Min; // Upper-left
534 ImVec2 Max; // Lower-right
535
536 constexpr ImRect() : Min(0.0f, 0.0f), Max(0.0f, 0.0f) {}
537 constexpr ImRect(const ImVec2& min, const ImVec2& max) : Min(min), Max(max) {}
538 constexpr ImRect(const ImVec4& v) : Min(v.x, v.y), Max(v.z, v.w) {}
539 constexpr ImRect(float x1, float y1, float x2, float y2) : Min(x1, y1), Max(x2, y2) {}
540
541 ImVec2 GetCenter() const { return ImVec2((Min.x + Max.x) * 0.5f, (Min.y + Max.y) * 0.5f); }
542 ImVec2 GetSize() const { return ImVec2(Max.x - Min.x, Max.y - Min.y); }
543 float GetWidth() const { return Max.x - Min.x; }
544 float GetHeight() const { return Max.y - Min.y; }
545 float GetArea() const { return (Max.x - Min.x) * (Max.y - Min.y); }
546 ImVec2 GetTL() const { return Min; } // Top-left
547 ImVec2 GetTR() const { return ImVec2(Max.x, Min.y); } // Top-right
548 ImVec2 GetBL() const { return ImVec2(Min.x, Max.y); } // Bottom-left
549 ImVec2 GetBR() const { return Max; } // Bottom-right
550 bool Contains(const ImVec2& p) const { return p.x >= Min.x && p.y >= Min.y && p.x < Max.x && p.y < Max.y; }
551 bool Contains(const ImRect& r) const { return r.Min.x >= Min.x && r.Min.y >= Min.y && r.Max.x <= Max.x && r.Max.y <= Max.y; }
552 bool ContainsWithPad(const ImVec2& p, const ImVec2& pad) const { return p.x >= Min.x - pad.x && p.y >= Min.y - pad.y && p.x < Max.x + pad.x && p.y < Max.y + pad.y; }
553 bool Overlaps(const ImRect& r) const { return r.Min.y < Max.y && r.Max.y > Min.y && r.Min.x < Max.x && r.Max.x > Min.x; }
554 void Add(const ImVec2& p) { if (Min.x > p.x) Min.x = p.x; if (Min.y > p.y) Min.y = p.y; if (Max.x < p.x) Max.x = p.x; if (Max.y < p.y) Max.y = p.y; }
555 void Add(const ImRect& r) { if (Min.x > r.Min.x) Min.x = r.Min.x; if (Min.y > r.Min.y) Min.y = r.Min.y; if (Max.x < r.Max.x) Max.x = r.Max.x; if (Max.y < r.Max.y) Max.y = r.Max.y; }
556 void Expand(const float amount) { Min.x -= amount; Min.y -= amount; Max.x += amount; Max.y += amount; }
557 void Expand(const ImVec2& amount) { Min.x -= amount.x; Min.y -= amount.y; Max.x += amount.x; Max.y += amount.y; }
558 void Translate(const ImVec2& d) { Min.x += d.x; Min.y += d.y; Max.x += d.x; Max.y += d.y; }
559 void TranslateX(float dx) { Min.x += dx; Max.x += dx; }
560 void TranslateY(float dy) { Min.y += dy; Max.y += dy; }
561 void ClipWith(const ImRect& r) { Min = ImMax(Min, r.Min); Max = ImMin(Max, r.Max); } // Simple version, may lead to an inverted rectangle, which is fine for Contains/Overlaps test but not for display.
562 void ClipWithFull(const ImRect& r) { Min = ImClamp(Min, r.Min, r.Max); Max = ImClamp(Max, r.Min, r.Max); } // Full version, ensure both points are fully clipped.
563 void Floor() { Min.x = IM_TRUNC(Min.x); Min.y = IM_TRUNC(Min.y); Max.x = IM_TRUNC(Max.x); Max.y = IM_TRUNC(Max.y); }
564 bool IsInverted() const { return Min.x > Max.x || Min.y > Max.y; }
565 ImVec4 ToVec4() const { return ImVec4(Min.x, Min.y, Max.x, Max.y); }
566};
567
568// Helper: ImBitArray
569#define IM_BITARRAY_TESTBIT(_ARRAY, _N) ((_ARRAY[(_N) >> 5] & ((ImU32)1 << ((_N) & 31))) != 0) // Macro version of ImBitArrayTestBit(): ensure args have side-effect or are costly!
570#define IM_BITARRAY_CLEARBIT(_ARRAY, _N) ((_ARRAY[(_N) >> 5] &= ~((ImU32)1 << ((_N) & 31)))) // Macro version of ImBitArrayClearBit(): ensure args have side-effect or are costly!
571inline size_t ImBitArrayGetStorageSizeInBytes(int bitcount) { return (size_t)((bitcount + 31) >> 5) << 2; }
572inline void ImBitArrayClearAllBits(ImU32* arr, int bitcount){ memset(arr, 0, ImBitArrayGetStorageSizeInBytes(bitcount)); }
573inline bool ImBitArrayTestBit(const ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); return (arr[n >> 5] & mask) != 0; }
574inline void ImBitArrayClearBit(ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); arr[n >> 5] &= ~mask; }
575inline void ImBitArraySetBit(ImU32* arr, int n) { ImU32 mask = (ImU32)1 << (n & 31); arr[n >> 5] |= mask; }
576inline void ImBitArraySetBitRange(ImU32* arr, int n, int n2) // Works on range [n..n2)
577{
578 n2--;
579 while (n <= n2)
580 {
581 int a_mod = (n & 31);
582 int b_mod = (n2 > (n | 31) ? 31 : (n2 & 31)) + 1;
583 ImU32 mask = (ImU32)(((ImU64)1 << b_mod) - 1) & ~(ImU32)(((ImU64)1 << a_mod) - 1);
584 arr[n >> 5] |= mask;
585 n = (n + 32) & ~31;
586 }
587}
588
589typedef ImU32* ImBitArrayPtr; // Name for use in structs
590
591// Helper: ImBitArray class (wrapper over ImBitArray functions)
592// Store 1-bit per value.
593template<int BITCOUNT, int OFFSET = 0>
594struct ImBitArray
595{
596 ImU32 Storage[(BITCOUNT + 31) >> 5];
597 ImBitArray() { ClearAllBits(); }
598 void ClearAllBits() { memset(Storage, 0, sizeof(Storage)); }
599 void SetAllBits() { memset(Storage, 255, sizeof(Storage)); }
600 bool TestBit(int n) const { n += OFFSET; IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < BITCOUNT); return IM_BITARRAY_TESTBIT(Storage, n); }
601 void SetBit(int n) { n += OFFSET; IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < BITCOUNT); ImBitArraySetBit(Storage, n); }
602 void ClearBit(int n) { n += OFFSET; IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < BITCOUNT); ImBitArrayClearBit(Storage, n); }
603 void SetBitRange(int n, int n2) { n += OFFSET; n2 += OFFSET; IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < BITCOUNT && n2 > n && n2 <= BITCOUNT); ImBitArraySetBitRange(Storage, n, n2); } // Works on range [n..n2)
604 bool operator[](int n) const { n += OFFSET; IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < BITCOUNT); return IM_BITARRAY_TESTBIT(Storage, n); }
605};
606
607// Helper: ImBitVector
608// Store 1-bit per value.
609struct IMGUI_API ImBitVector
610{
611 ImVector<ImU32> Storage;
612 void Create(int sz) { Storage.resize((sz + 31) >> 5); memset(Storage.Data, 0, (size_t)Storage.Size * sizeof(Storage.Data[0])); }
613 void Clear() { Storage.clear(); }
614 bool TestBit(int n) const { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); return IM_BITARRAY_TESTBIT(Storage.Data, n); }
615 void SetBit(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); ImBitArraySetBit(Storage.Data, n); }
616 void ClearBit(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n < (Storage.Size << 5)); ImBitArrayClearBit(Storage.Data, n); }
617};

620// Helper: ImSpan<>
621// Pointing to a span of data we don't own.
622template<typename T>
623struct ImSpan
624{
625 T* Data;
626 T* DataEnd;
627
628 // Constructors, destructor
629 inline ImSpan() { Data = DataEnd = NULL; }
630 inline ImSpan(T* data, int size) { Data = data; DataEnd = data + size; }
631 inline ImSpan(T* data, T* data_end) { Data = data; DataEnd = data_end; }
632
633 inline void set(T* data, int size) { Data = data; DataEnd = data + size; }
634 inline void set(T* data, T* data_end) { Data = data; DataEnd = data_end; }
635 inline int size() const { return (int)(ptrdiff_t)(DataEnd - Data); }
636 inline int size_in_bytes() const { return (int)(ptrdiff_t)(DataEnd - Data) * (int)sizeof(T); }
637 inline T& operator[](int i) { T* p = Data + i; IM_ASSERT(p >= Data && p < DataEnd); return *p; }
638 inline const T& operator[](int i) const { const T* p = Data + i; IM_ASSERT(p >= Data && p < DataEnd); return *p; }
639
640 inline T* begin() { return Data; }
641 inline const T* begin() const { return Data; }
642 inline T* end() { return DataEnd; }
643 inline const T* end() const { return DataEnd; }
644
645 // Utilities
646 inline int index_from_ptr(const T* it) const { IM_ASSERT(it >= Data && it < DataEnd); const ptrdiff_t off = it - Data; return (int)off; }
647};
648
649// Helper: ImSpanAllocator<>
650// Facilitate storing multiple chunks into a single large block (the "arena")
651// - Usage: call Reserve() N times, allocate GetArenaSizeInBytes() worth, pass it to SetArenaBasePtr(), call GetSpan() N times to retrieve the aligned ranges.
652template<int CHUNKS>
653struct ImSpanAllocator
654{
655 char* BasePtr;
656 int CurrOff;
657 int CurrIdx;
658 int Offsets[CHUNKS];
659 int Sizes[CHUNKS];
660
661 ImSpanAllocator() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); }
662 inline void Reserve(int n, size_t sz, int a=4) { IM_ASSERT(n == CurrIdx && n < CHUNKS); CurrOff = IM_MEMALIGN(CurrOff, a); Offsets[n] = CurrOff; Sizes[n] = (int)sz; CurrIdx++; CurrOff += (int)sz; }
663 inline int GetArenaSizeInBytes() { return CurrOff; }
664 inline void SetArenaBasePtr(void* base_ptr) { BasePtr = (char*)base_ptr; }
665 inline void* GetSpanPtrBegin(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < CHUNKS && CurrIdx == CHUNKS); return (void*)(BasePtr + Offsets[n]); }
666 inline void* GetSpanPtrEnd(int n) { IM_ASSERT(n >= 0 && n < CHUNKS && CurrIdx == CHUNKS); return (void*)(BasePtr + Offsets[n] + Sizes[n]); }
667 template<typename T>
668 inline void GetSpan(int n, ImSpan<T>* span) { span->set((T*)GetSpanPtrBegin(n), (T*)GetSpanPtrEnd(n)); }
669};
670
671// Helper: ImPool<>
672// Basic keyed storage for contiguous instances, slow/amortized insertion, O(1) indexable, O(Log N) queries by ID over a dense/hot buffer,
673// Honor constructor/destructor. Add/remove invalidate all pointers. Indexes have the same lifetime as the associated object.
674typedef int ImPoolIdx;
675template<typename T>
676struct ImPool
677{
678 ImVector<T> Buf; // Contiguous data
679 ImGuiStorage Map; // ID->Index
680 ImPoolIdx FreeIdx; // Next free idx to use
681 ImPoolIdx AliveCount; // Number of active/alive items (for display purpose)
682
683 ImPool() { FreeIdx = AliveCount = 0; }
684 ~ImPool() { Clear(); }
685 T* GetByKey(ImGuiID key) { int idx = Map.GetInt(key, -1); return (idx != -1) ? &Buf[idx] : NULL; }
686 T* GetByIndex(ImPoolIdx n) { return &Buf[n]; }
687 ImPoolIdx GetIndex(const T* p) const { IM_ASSERT(p >= Buf.Data && p < Buf.Data + Buf.Size); return (ImPoolIdx)(p - Buf.Data); }
688 T* GetOrAddByKey(ImGuiID key) { int* p_idx = Map.GetIntRef(key, -1); if (*p_idx != -1) return &Buf[*p_idx]; *p_idx = FreeIdx; return Add(); }
689 bool Contains(const T* p) const { return (p >= Buf.Data && p < Buf.Data + Buf.Size); }
690 void Clear() { for (int n = 0; n < Map.Data.Size; n++) { int idx = Map.Data[n].val_i; if (idx != -1) Buf[idx].~T(); } Map.Clear(); Buf.clear(); FreeIdx = AliveCount = 0; }
691 T* Add() { int idx = FreeIdx; if (idx == Buf.Size) { Buf.resize(Buf.Size + 1); FreeIdx++; } else { FreeIdx = *(int*)&Buf[idx]; } IM_PLACEMENT_NEW(&Buf[idx]) T(); AliveCount++; return &Buf[idx]; }
692 void Remove(ImGuiID key, const T* p) { Remove(key, GetIndex(p)); }
693 void Remove(ImGuiID key, ImPoolIdx idx) { Buf[idx].~T(); *(int*)&Buf[idx] = FreeIdx; FreeIdx = idx; Map.SetInt(key, -1); AliveCount--; }
694 void Reserve(int capacity) { Buf.reserve(capacity); Map.Data.reserve(capacity); }
695
696 // To iterate a ImPool: for (int n = 0; n < pool.GetMapSize(); n++) if (T* t = pool.TryGetMapData(n)) { ... }
697 // Can be avoided if you know .Remove() has never been called on the pool, or AliveCount == GetMapSize()
698 int GetAliveCount() const { return AliveCount; } // Number of active/alive items in the pool (for display purpose)
699 int GetBufSize() const { return Buf.Size; }
700 int GetMapSize() const { return Map.Data.Size; } // It is the map we need iterate to find valid items, since we don't have "alive" storage anywhere
701 T* TryGetMapData(ImPoolIdx n) { int idx = Map.Data[n].val_i; if (idx == -1) return NULL; return GetByIndex(idx); }
702#ifndef IMGUI_DISABLE_OBSOLETE_FUNCTIONS
703 int GetSize() { return GetMapSize(); } // For ImPlot: should use GetMapSize() from (IMGUI_VERSION_NUM >= 18304)
704#endif
705};
706
707// Helper: ImChunkStream<>
708// Build and iterate a contiguous stream of variable-sized structures.
709// This is used by Settings to store persistent data while reducing allocation count.
710// We store the chunk size first, and align the final size on 4 bytes boundaries.
711// The tedious/zealous amount of casting is to avoid -Wcast-align warnings.
712template<typename T>
713struct ImChunkStream
714{
715 ImVector<char> Buf;
716
717 void clear() { Buf.clear(); }
718 bool empty() const { return Buf.Size == 0; }
719 int size() const { return Buf.Size; }
720 T* alloc_chunk(size_t sz) { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; sz = IM_MEMALIGN(HDR_SZ + sz, 4u); int off = Buf.Size; Buf.resize(off + (int)sz); ((int*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off))[0] = (int)sz; return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off + (int)HDR_SZ); }
721 T* begin() { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; if (!Buf.Data) return NULL; return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + HDR_SZ); }
722 T* next_chunk(T* p) { size_t HDR_SZ = 4; IM_ASSERT(p >= begin() && p < end()); p = (T*)(void*)((char*)(void*)p + chunk_size(p)); if (p == (T*)(void*)((char*)end() + HDR_SZ)) return (T*)0; IM_ASSERT(p < end()); return p; }
723 int chunk_size(const T* p) { return ((const int*)p)[-1]; }
724 T* end() { return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + Buf.Size); }
725 int offset_from_ptr(const T* p) { IM_ASSERT(p >= begin() && p < end()); const ptrdiff_t off = (const char*)p - Buf.Data; return (int)off; }
726 T* ptr_from_offset(int off) { IM_ASSERT(off >= 4 && off < Buf.Size); return (T*)(void*)(Buf.Data + off); }
727 void swap(ImChunkStream<T>& rhs) { rhs.Buf.swap(Buf); }
728};
729
730// Helper: ImGuiTextIndex<>
731// Maintain a line index for a text buffer. This is a strong candidate to be moved into the public API.
732struct ImGuiTextIndex
733{
734 ImVector<int> LineOffsets;
735 int EndOffset = 0; // Because we don't own text buffer we need to maintain EndOffset (may bake in LineOffsets?)
736
737 void clear() { LineOffsets.clear(); EndOffset = 0; }
738 int size() { return LineOffsets.Size; }
739 const char* get_line_begin(const char* base, int n) { return base + LineOffsets[n]; }
740 const char* get_line_end(const char* base, int n) { return base + (n + 1 < LineOffsets.Size ? (LineOffsets[n + 1] - 1) : EndOffset); }
741 void append(const char* base, int old_size, int new_size);
742};

744//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
745// [SECTION] ImDrawList support
746//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
747
748// ImDrawList: Helper function to calculate a circle's segment count given its radius and a "maximum error" value.
749// Estimation of number of circle segment based on error is derived using method described in https://stackoverflow.com/a/2244088/15194693
750// Number of segments (N) is calculated using equation:
751// N = ceil ( pi / acos(1 - error / r) ) where r > 0, error <= r
752// Our equation is significantly simpler that one in the post thanks for choosing segment that is
753// perpendicular to X axis. Follow steps in the article from this starting condition and you will
754// will get this result.
755//
756// Rendering circles with an odd number of segments, while mathematically correct will produce
757// asymmetrical results on the raster grid. Therefore we're rounding N to next even number (7->8, 8->8, 9->10 etc.)
758#define IM_ROUNDUP_TO_EVEN(_V) ((((_V) + 1) / 2) * 2)
759#define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_MIN 4
760#define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_MAX 512
761#define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_CALC(_RAD,_MAXERROR) ImClamp(IM_ROUNDUP_TO_EVEN((int)ImCeil(IM_PI / ImAcos(1 - ImMin((_MAXERROR), (_RAD)) / (_RAD)))), IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_MIN, IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_MAX)
762
763// Raw equation from IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_CALC rewritten for 'r' and 'error'.
764#define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_CALC_R(_N,_MAXERROR) ((_MAXERROR) / (1 - ImCos(IM_PI / ImMax((float)(_N), IM_PI))))
765#define IM_DRAWLIST_CIRCLE_AUTO_SEGMENT_CALC_ERROR(_N,_RAD) ((1 - ImCos(IM_PI / ImMax((float)(_N), IM_PI))) / (_RAD))
766
767// ImDrawList: Lookup table size for adaptive arc drawing, cover full circle.
768#ifndef IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_TABLE_SIZE
769#define IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_TABLE_SIZE 48 // Number of samples in lookup table.
770#endif
771#define IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_SAMPLE_MAX IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_TABLE_SIZE // Sample index _PathArcToFastEx() for 360 angle.
772
773// Data shared between all ImDrawList instances
774// You may want to create your own instance of this if you want to use ImDrawList completely without ImGui. In that case, watch out for future changes to this structure.
775struct IMGUI_API ImDrawListSharedData
776{
777 ImVec2 TexUvWhitePixel; // UV of white pixel in the atlas
778 ImFont* Font; // Current/default font (optional, for simplified AddText overload)
779 float FontSize; // Current/default font size (optional, for simplified AddText overload)
780 float CurveTessellationTol; // Tessellation tolerance when using PathBezierCurveTo()
781 float CircleSegmentMaxError; // Number of circle segments to use per pixel of radius for AddCircle() etc
782 ImVec4 ClipRectFullscreen; // Value for PushClipRectFullscreen()
783 ImDrawListFlags InitialFlags; // Initial flags at the beginning of the frame (it is possible to alter flags on a per-drawlist basis afterwards)
784
785 // [Internal] Temp write buffer
786 ImVector<ImVec2> TempBuffer;
787
788 // [Internal] Lookup tables
789 ImVec2 ArcFastVtx[IM_DRAWLIST_ARCFAST_TABLE_SIZE]; // Sample points on the quarter of the circle.
790 float ArcFastRadiusCutoff; // Cutoff radius after which arc drawing will fallback to slower PathArcTo()
791 ImU8 CircleSegmentCounts[64]; // Precomputed segment count for given radius before we calculate it dynamically (to avoid calculation overhead)
792 const ImVec4* TexUvLines; // UV of anti-aliased lines in the atlas
793
794 ImDrawListSharedData();
795 void SetCircleTessellationMaxError(float max_error);
796};

1110// Internal state of the currently focused/edited text input box
1111// For a given item ID, access with ImGui::GetInputTextState()
1112struct IMGUI_API ImGuiInputTextState
1113{
1114 ImGuiContext* Ctx; // parent UI context (needs to be set explicitly by parent).
1115 ImGuiID ID; // widget id owning the text state
1116 int CurLenW, CurLenA; // we need to maintain our buffer length in both UTF-8 and wchar format. UTF-8 length is valid even if TextA is not.
1117 ImVector<ImWchar> TextW; // edit buffer, we need to persist but can't guarantee the persistence of the user-provided buffer. so we copy into own buffer.
1118 ImVector<char> TextA; // temporary UTF8 buffer for callbacks and other operations. this is not updated in every code-path! size=capacity.
1119 ImVector<char> InitialTextA; // backup of end-user buffer at the time of focus (in UTF-8, unaltered)
1120 bool TextAIsValid; // temporary UTF8 buffer is not initially valid before we make the widget active (until then we pull the data from user argument)
1121 int BufCapacityA; // end-user buffer capacity
1122 float ScrollX; // horizontal scrolling/offset
1123 ImStb::STB_TexteditState Stb; // state for stb_textedit.h
1124 float CursorAnim; // timer for cursor blink, reset on every user action so the cursor reappears immediately
1125 bool CursorFollow; // set when we want scrolling to follow the current cursor position (not always!)
1126 bool SelectedAllMouseLock; // after a double-click to select all, we ignore further mouse drags to update selection
1127 bool Edited; // edited this frame
1128 ImGuiInputTextFlags Flags; // copy of InputText() flags. may be used to check if e.g. ImGuiInputTextFlags_Password is set.
1129
1130 ImGuiInputTextState() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); }
1131 void ClearText() { CurLenW = CurLenA = 0; TextW[0] = 0; TextA[0] = 0; CursorClamp(); }
1132 void ClearFreeMemory() { TextW.clear(); TextA.clear(); InitialTextA.clear(); }
1133 int GetUndoAvailCount() const { return Stb.undostate.undo_point; }
1134 int GetRedoAvailCount() const { return STB_TEXTEDIT_UNDOSTATECOUNT - Stb.undostate.redo_point; }
1135 void OnKeyPressed(int key); // Cannot be inline because we call in code in stb_textedit.h implementation
1136
1137 // Cursor & Selection
1138 void CursorAnimReset() { CursorAnim = -0.30f; } // After a user-input the cursor stays on for a while without blinking
1139 void CursorClamp() { Stb.cursor = ImMin(Stb.cursor, CurLenW); Stb.select_start = ImMin(Stb.select_start, CurLenW); Stb.select_end = ImMin(Stb.select_end, CurLenW); }
1140 bool HasSelection() const { return Stb.select_start != Stb.select_end; }
1141 void ClearSelection() { Stb.select_start = Stb.select_end = Stb.cursor; }
1142 int GetCursorPos() const { return Stb.cursor; }
1143 int GetSelectionStart() const { return Stb.select_start; }
1144 int GetSelectionEnd() const { return Stb.select_end; }
1145 void SelectAll() { Stb.select_start = 0; Stb.cursor = Stb.select_end = CurLenW; Stb.has_preferred_x = 0; }
1146};

1380// Input function taking an 'ImGuiID owner_id' argument defaults to (ImGuiKeyOwner_Any == 0) aka don't test ownership, which matches legacy behavior.
1381#define ImGuiKeyOwner_Any ((ImGuiID)0) // Accept key that have an owner, UNLESS a call to SetKeyOwner() explicitly used ImGuiInputFlags_LockThisFrame or ImGuiInputFlags_LockUntilRelease.
1382#define ImGuiKeyOwner_None ((ImGuiID)-1) // Require key to have no owner.
1383
1384typedef ImS16 ImGuiKeyRoutingIndex;
1385
1386// Routing table entry (sizeof() == 16 bytes)
1387struct ImGuiKeyRoutingData
1388{
1389 ImGuiKeyRoutingIndex NextEntryIndex;
1390 ImU16 Mods; // Technically we'd only need 4-bits but for simplify we store ImGuiMod_ values which need 16-bits. ImGuiMod_Shortcut is already translated to Ctrl/Super.
1391 ImU8 RoutingNextScore; // Lower is better (0: perfect score)
1392 ImGuiID RoutingCurr;
1393 ImGuiID RoutingNext;
1394
1395 ImGuiKeyRoutingData() { NextEntryIndex = -1; Mods = 0; RoutingNextScore = 255; RoutingCurr = RoutingNext = ImGuiKeyOwner_None; }
1396};
1397
1398// Routing table: maintain a desired owner for each possible key-chord (key + mods), and setup owner in NewFrame() when mods are matching.
1399// Stored in main context (1 instance)
1400struct ImGuiKeyRoutingTable
1401{
1402 ImGuiKeyRoutingIndex Index[ImGuiKey_NamedKey_COUNT]; // Index of first entry in Entries[]
1403 ImVector<ImGuiKeyRoutingData> Entries;
1404 ImVector<ImGuiKeyRoutingData> EntriesNext; // Double-buffer to avoid reallocation (could use a shared buffer)
1405
1406 ImGuiKeyRoutingTable() { Clear(); }
1407 void Clear() { for (int n = 0; n < IM_ARRAYSIZE(Index); n++) Index[n] = -1; Entries.clear(); EntriesNext.clear(); }
1408};

1410// This extends ImGuiKeyData but only for named keys (legacy keys don't support the new features)
1411// Stored in main context (1 per named key). In the future it might be merged into ImGuiKeyData.
1412struct ImGuiKeyOwnerData
1413{
1414 ImGuiID OwnerCurr;
1415 ImGuiID OwnerNext;
1416 bool LockThisFrame; // Reading this key requires explicit owner id (until end of frame). Set by ImGuiInputFlags_LockThisFrame.
1417 bool LockUntilRelease; // Reading this key requires explicit owner id (until key is released). Set by ImGuiInputFlags_LockUntilRelease. When this is true LockThisFrame is always true as well.
1418
1419 ImGuiKeyOwnerData() { OwnerCurr = OwnerNext = ImGuiKeyOwner_None; LockThisFrame = LockUntilRelease = false; }
1420};

1422// Flags for extended versions of IsKeyPressed(), IsMouseClicked(), Shortcut(), SetKeyOwner(), SetItemKeyOwner()
1423// Don't mistake with ImGuiInputTextFlags! (for ImGui::InputText() function)
1424enum ImGuiInputFlags_
1425{
1426 // Flags for IsKeyPressed(), IsMouseClicked(), Shortcut()
1427 ImGuiInputFlags_None = 0,
1428 ImGuiInputFlags_Repeat = 1 << 0, // Return true on successive repeats. Default for legacy IsKeyPressed(). NOT Default for legacy IsMouseClicked(). MUST BE == 1.
1429 ImGuiInputFlags_RepeatRateDefault = 1 << 1, // Repeat rate: Regular (default)
1430 ImGuiInputFlags_RepeatRateNavMove = 1 << 2, // Repeat rate: Fast
1431 ImGuiInputFlags_RepeatRateNavTweak = 1 << 3, // Repeat rate: Faster
1432 ImGuiInputFlags_RepeatRateMask_ = ImGuiInputFlags_RepeatRateDefault | ImGuiInputFlags_RepeatRateNavMove | ImGuiInputFlags_RepeatRateNavTweak,
1433
1434 // Flags for SetItemKeyOwner()
1435 ImGuiInputFlags_CondHovered = 1 << 4, // Only set if item is hovered (default to both)
1436 ImGuiInputFlags_CondActive = 1 << 5, // Only set if item is active (default to both)
1437 ImGuiInputFlags_CondDefault_ = ImGuiInputFlags_CondHovered | ImGuiInputFlags_CondActive,
1438 ImGuiInputFlags_CondMask_ = ImGuiInputFlags_CondHovered | ImGuiInputFlags_CondActive,
1439
1440 // Flags for SetKeyOwner(), SetItemKeyOwner()
1441 ImGuiInputFlags_LockThisFrame = 1 << 6, // Access to key data will require EXPLICIT owner ID (ImGuiKeyOwner_Any/0 will NOT accepted for polling). Cleared at end of frame. This is useful to make input-owner-aware code steal keys from non-input-owner-aware code.
1442 ImGuiInputFlags_LockUntilRelease = 1 << 7, // Access to key data will require EXPLICIT owner ID (ImGuiKeyOwner_Any/0 will NOT accepted for polling). Cleared when the key is released or at end of each frame if key is released. This is useful to make input-owner-aware code steal keys from non-input-owner-aware code.
1443
1444 // Routing policies for Shortcut() + low-level SetShortcutRouting()
1445 // - The general idea is that several callers register interest in a shortcut, and only one owner gets it.
1446 // - When a policy (other than _RouteAlways) is set, Shortcut() will register itself with SetShortcutRouting(),
1447 // allowing the system to decide where to route the input among other route-aware calls.
1448 // - Shortcut() uses ImGuiInputFlags_RouteFocused by default: meaning that a simple Shortcut() poll
1449 // will register a route and only succeed when parent window is in the focus stack and if no-one
1450 // with a higher priority is claiming the shortcut.
1451 // - Using ImGuiInputFlags_RouteAlways is roughly equivalent to doing e.g. IsKeyPressed(key) + testing mods.
1452 // - Priorities: GlobalHigh > Focused (when owner is active item) > Global > Focused (when focused window) > GlobalLow.
1453 // - Can select only 1 policy among all available.
1454 ImGuiInputFlags_RouteFocused = 1 << 8, // (Default) Register focused route: Accept inputs if window is in focus stack. Deep-most focused window takes inputs. ActiveId takes inputs over deep-most focused window.
1455 ImGuiInputFlags_RouteGlobalLow = 1 << 9, // Register route globally (lowest priority: unless a focused window or active item registered the route) -> recommended Global priority.
1456 ImGuiInputFlags_RouteGlobal = 1 << 10, // Register route globally (medium priority: unless an active item registered the route, e.g. CTRL+A registered by InputText).
1457 ImGuiInputFlags_RouteGlobalHigh = 1 << 11, // Register route globally (highest priority: unlikely you need to use that: will interfere with every active items)
1458 ImGuiInputFlags_RouteMask_ = ImGuiInputFlags_RouteFocused | ImGuiInputFlags_RouteGlobal | ImGuiInputFlags_RouteGlobalLow | ImGuiInputFlags_RouteGlobalHigh, // _Always not part of this!
1459 ImGuiInputFlags_RouteAlways = 1 << 12, // Do not register route, poll keys directly.
1460 ImGuiInputFlags_RouteUnlessBgFocused= 1 << 13, // Global routes will not be applied if underlying background/void is focused (== no Dear ImGui windows are focused). Useful for overlay applications.
1461 ImGuiInputFlags_RouteExtraMask_ = ImGuiInputFlags_RouteAlways | ImGuiInputFlags_RouteUnlessBgFocused,
1462
1463 // [Internal] Mask of which function support which flags
1464 ImGuiInputFlags_SupportedByIsKeyPressed = ImGuiInputFlags_Repeat | ImGuiInputFlags_RepeatRateMask_,
1465 ImGuiInputFlags_SupportedByShortcut = ImGuiInputFlags_Repeat | ImGuiInputFlags_RepeatRateMask_ | ImGuiInputFlags_RouteMask_ | ImGuiInputFlags_RouteExtraMask_,
1466 ImGuiInputFlags_SupportedBySetKeyOwner = ImGuiInputFlags_LockThisFrame | ImGuiInputFlags_LockUntilRelease,
1467 ImGuiInputFlags_SupportedBySetItemKeyOwner = ImGuiInputFlags_SupportedBySetKeyOwner | ImGuiInputFlags_CondMask_,
1468};

1584// Flags for GetTypingSelectRequest()
1585enum ImGuiTypingSelectFlags_
1586{
1587 ImGuiTypingSelectFlags_None = 0,
1588 ImGuiTypingSelectFlags_AllowBackspace = 1 << 0, // Backspace to delete character inputs. If using: ensure GetTypingSelectRequest() is not called more than once per frame (filter by e.g. focus state)
1589 ImGuiTypingSelectFlags_AllowSingleCharMode = 1 << 1, // Allow "single char" search mode which is activated when pressing the same character multiple times.
1590};
1591
1592// Returned by GetTypingSelectRequest(), designed to eventually be public.
1593struct IMGUI_API ImGuiTypingSelectRequest
1594{
1595 ImGuiTypingSelectFlags Flags; // Flags passed to GetTypingSelectRequest()
1596 int SearchBufferLen;
1597 const char* SearchBuffer; // Search buffer contents (use full string. unless SingleCharMode is set, in which case use SingleCharSize).
1598 bool SelectRequest; // Set when buffer was modified this frame, requesting a selection.
1599 bool SingleCharMode; // Notify when buffer contains same character repeated, to implement special mode. In this situation it preferred to not display any on-screen search indication.
1600 ImS8 SingleCharSize; // Length in bytes of first letter codepoint (1 for ascii, 2-4 for UTF-8). If (SearchBufferLen==RepeatCharSize) only 1 letter has been input.
1601};
1602
1603// Storage for GetTypingSelectRequest()
1604struct IMGUI_API ImGuiTypingSelectState
1605{
1606 ImGuiTypingSelectRequest Request; // User-facing data
1607 char SearchBuffer[64]; // Search buffer: no need to make dynamic as this search is very transient.
1608 ImGuiID FocusScope;
1609 int LastRequestFrame = 0;
1610 float LastRequestTime = 0.0f;
1611 bool SingleCharModeLock = false; // After a certain single char repeat count we lock into SingleCharMode. Two benefits: 1) buffer never fill, 2) we can provide an immediate SingleChar mode without timer elapsing.
1612
1613 ImGuiTypingSelectState() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); }
1614 void Clear() { SearchBuffer[0] = 0; SingleCharModeLock = false; } // We preserve remaining data for easier debugging
1615};

1693// Extend ImGuiDockNodeFlags_
1694enum ImGuiDockNodeFlagsPrivate_
1695{
1696 // [Internal]
1697 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_DockSpace = 1 << 10, // Saved // A dockspace is a node that occupy space within an existing user window. Otherwise the node is floating and create its own window.
1698 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_CentralNode = 1 << 11, // Saved // The central node has 2 main properties: stay visible when empty, only use "remaining" spaces from its neighbor.
1699 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoTabBar = 1 << 12, // Saved // Tab bar is completely unavailable. No triangle in the corner to enable it back.
1700 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_HiddenTabBar = 1 << 13, // Saved // Tab bar is hidden, with a triangle in the corner to show it again (NB: actual tab-bar instance may be destroyed as this is only used for single-window tab bar)
1701 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoWindowMenuButton = 1 << 14, // Saved // Disable window/docking menu (that one that appears instead of the collapse button)
1702 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoCloseButton = 1 << 15, // Saved // Disable close button
1703 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResizeX = 1 << 16, // //
1704 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResizeY = 1 << 17, // //
1705 // Disable docking/undocking actions in this dockspace or individual node (existing docked nodes will be preserved)
1706 // Those are not exposed in public because the desirable sharing/inheriting/copy-flag-on-split behaviors are quite difficult to design and understand.
1707 // The two public flags ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingOverCentralNode/ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingSplit don't have those issues.
1708 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingSplitOther = 1 << 19, // // Disable this node from splitting other windows/nodes.
1709 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingOverMe = 1 << 20, // // Disable other windows/nodes from being docked over this node.
1710 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingOverOther = 1 << 21, // // Disable this node from being docked over another window or non-empty node.
1711 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingOverEmpty = 1 << 22, // // Disable this node from being docked over an empty node (e.g. DockSpace with no other windows)
1712 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDocking = ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingOverMe | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingOverOther | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingOverEmpty | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingSplit | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingSplitOther,
1713 // Masks
1714 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_SharedFlagsInheritMask_ = ~0,
1715 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResizeFlagsMask_ = ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResize | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResizeX | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResizeY,
1716 // When splitting, those local flags are moved to the inheriting child, never duplicated
1717 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_LocalFlagsTransferMask_ = ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoDockingSplit | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResizeFlagsMask_ | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_AutoHideTabBar | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_CentralNode | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoTabBar | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_HiddenTabBar | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoWindowMenuButton | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoCloseButton,
1718 ImGuiDockNodeFlags_SavedFlagsMask_ = ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoResizeFlagsMask_ | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_DockSpace | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_CentralNode | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoTabBar | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_HiddenTabBar | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoWindowMenuButton | ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoCloseButton,
1719};

1737// sizeof() 156~192
1738struct IMGUI_API ImGuiDockNode
1739{
1740 ImGuiID ID;
1741 ImGuiDockNodeFlags SharedFlags; // (Write) Flags shared by all nodes of a same dockspace hierarchy (inherited from the root node)
1742 ImGuiDockNodeFlags LocalFlags; // (Write) Flags specific to this node
1743 ImGuiDockNodeFlags LocalFlagsInWindows; // (Write) Flags specific to this node, applied from windows
1744 ImGuiDockNodeFlags MergedFlags; // (Read) Effective flags (== SharedFlags | LocalFlagsInNode | LocalFlagsInWindows)
1745 ImGuiDockNodeState State;
1746 ImGuiDockNode* ParentNode;
1747 ImGuiDockNode* ChildNodes[2]; // [Split node only] Child nodes (left/right or top/bottom). Consider switching to an array.
1748 ImVector<ImGuiWindow*> Windows; // Note: unordered list! Iterate TabBar->Tabs for user-order.
1749 ImGuiTabBar* TabBar;
1750 ImVec2 Pos; // Current position
1751 ImVec2 Size; // Current size
1752 ImVec2 SizeRef; // [Split node only] Last explicitly written-to size (overridden when using a splitter affecting the node), used to calculate Size.
1753 ImGuiAxis SplitAxis; // [Split node only] Split axis (X or Y)
1754 ImGuiWindowClass WindowClass; // [Root node only]
1755 ImU32 LastBgColor;
1756
1757 ImGuiWindow* HostWindow;
1758 ImGuiWindow* VisibleWindow; // Generally point to window which is ID is == SelectedTabID, but when CTRL+Tabbing this can be a different window.
1759 ImGuiDockNode* CentralNode; // [Root node only] Pointer to central node.
1760 ImGuiDockNode* OnlyNodeWithWindows; // [Root node only] Set when there is a single visible node within the hierarchy.
1761 int CountNodeWithWindows; // [Root node only]
1762 int LastFrameAlive; // Last frame number the node was updated or kept alive explicitly with DockSpace() + ImGuiDockNodeFlags_KeepAliveOnly
1763 int LastFrameActive; // Last frame number the node was updated.
1764 int LastFrameFocused; // Last frame number the node was focused.
1765 ImGuiID LastFocusedNodeId; // [Root node only] Which of our child docking node (any ancestor in the hierarchy) was last focused.
1766 ImGuiID SelectedTabId; // [Leaf node only] Which of our tab/window is selected.
1767 ImGuiID WantCloseTabId; // [Leaf node only] Set when closing a specific tab/window.
1768 ImGuiID RefViewportId; // Reference viewport ID from visible window when HostWindow == NULL.
1769 ImGuiDataAuthority AuthorityForPos :3;
1770 ImGuiDataAuthority AuthorityForSize :3;
1771 ImGuiDataAuthority AuthorityForViewport :3;
1772 bool IsVisible :1; // Set to false when the node is hidden (usually disabled as it has no active window)
1773 bool IsFocused :1;
1774 bool IsBgDrawnThisFrame :1;
1775 bool HasCloseButton :1; // Provide space for a close button (if any of the docked window has one). Note that button may be hidden on window without one.
1776 bool HasWindowMenuButton :1;
1777 bool HasCentralNodeChild :1;
1778 bool WantCloseAll :1; // Set when closing all tabs at once.
1779 bool WantLockSizeOnce :1;
1780 bool WantMouseMove :1; // After a node extraction we need to transition toward moving the newly created host window
1781 bool WantHiddenTabBarUpdate :1;
1782 bool WantHiddenTabBarToggle :1;
1783
1784 ImGuiDockNode(ImGuiID id);
1785 ~ImGuiDockNode();
1786 bool IsRootNode() const { return ParentNode == NULL; }
1787 bool IsDockSpace() const { return (MergedFlags & ImGuiDockNodeFlags_DockSpace) != 0; }
1788 bool IsFloatingNode() const { return ParentNode == NULL && (MergedFlags & ImGuiDockNodeFlags_DockSpace) == 0; }
1789 bool IsCentralNode() const { return (MergedFlags & ImGuiDockNodeFlags_CentralNode) != 0; }
1790 bool IsHiddenTabBar() const { return (MergedFlags & ImGuiDockNodeFlags_HiddenTabBar) != 0; } // Hidden tab bar can be shown back by clicking the small triangle
1791 bool IsNoTabBar() const { return (MergedFlags & ImGuiDockNodeFlags_NoTabBar) != 0; } // Never show a tab bar
1792 bool IsSplitNode() const { return ChildNodes[0] != NULL; }
1793 bool IsLeafNode() const { return ChildNodes[0] == NULL; }
1794 bool IsEmpty() const { return ChildNodes[0] == NULL && Windows.Size == 0; }
1795 ImRect Rect() const { return ImRect(Pos.x, Pos.y, Pos.x + Size.x, Pos.y + Size.y); }
1796
1797 void SetLocalFlags(ImGuiDockNodeFlags flags) { LocalFlags = flags; UpdateMergedFlags(); }
1798 void UpdateMergedFlags() { MergedFlags = SharedFlags | LocalFlags | LocalFlagsInWindows; }
1799};

1801// List of colors that are stored at the time of Begin() into Docked Windows.

1804// but it would be more complex as we'd need to double-buffer both as e.g. drop target may refer to window from last frame.
1805enum ImGuiWindowDockStyleCol

1812 ImGuiWindowDockStyleCol_TabUnfocusedActive,
1813 ImGuiWindowDockStyleCol_COUNT
1814};

1819};

1832//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1833// [SECTION] Viewport support
1834//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1835
1836// ImGuiViewport Private/Internals fields (cardinal sin: we are using inheritance!)
1837// Every instance of ImGuiViewport is in fact a ImGuiViewportP.
1838struct ImGuiViewportP : public ImGuiViewport
1839{
1840 ImGuiWindow* Window; // Set when the viewport is owned by a window (and ImGuiViewportFlags_CanHostOtherWindows is NOT set)
1841 int Idx;
1842 int LastFrameActive; // Last frame number this viewport was activated by a window
1843 int LastFocusedStampCount; // Last stamp number from when a window hosted by this viewport was focused (by comparing this value between two viewport we have an implicit viewport z-order we use as fallback)
1844 ImGuiID LastNameHash;
1845 ImVec2 LastPos;
1846 float Alpha; // Window opacity (when dragging dockable windows/viewports we make them transparent)
1847 float LastAlpha;
1848 bool LastFocusedHadNavWindow;// Instead of maintaining a LastFocusedWindow (which may harder to correctly maintain), we merely store weither NavWindow != NULL last time the viewport was focused.
1849 short PlatformMonitor;
1850 int BgFgDrawListsLastFrame[2]; // Last frame number the background (0) and foreground (1) draw lists were used
1851 ImDrawList* BgFgDrawLists[2]; // Convenience background (0) and foreground (1) draw lists. We use them to draw software mouser cursor when io.MouseDrawCursor is set and to draw most debug overlays.
1852 ImDrawData DrawDataP;
1853 ImDrawDataBuilder DrawDataBuilder; // Temporary data while building final ImDrawData
1854 ImVec2 LastPlatformPos;
1855 ImVec2 LastPlatformSize;
1856 ImVec2 LastRendererSize;
1857 ImVec2 WorkOffsetMin; // Work Area: Offset from Pos to top-left corner of Work Area. Generally (0,0) or (0,+main_menu_bar_height). Work Area is Full Area but without menu-bars/status-bars (so WorkArea always fit inside Pos/Size!)
1858 ImVec2 WorkOffsetMax; // Work Area: Offset from Pos+Size to bottom-right corner of Work Area. Generally (0,0) or (0,-status_bar_height).
1859 ImVec2 BuildWorkOffsetMin; // Work Area: Offset being built during current frame. Generally >= 0.0f.
1860 ImVec2 BuildWorkOffsetMax; // Work Area: Offset being built during current frame. Generally <= 0.0f.
1861
1862 ImGuiViewportP() { Window = NULL; Idx = -1; LastFrameActive = BgFgDrawListsLastFrame[0] = BgFgDrawListsLastFrame[1] = LastFocusedStampCount = -1; LastNameHash = 0; Alpha = LastAlpha = 1.0f; LastFocusedHadNavWindow = false; PlatformMonitor = -1; BgFgDrawLists[0] = BgFgDrawLists[1] = NULL; LastPlatformPos = LastPlatformSize = LastRendererSize = ImVec2(FLT_MAX, FLT_MAX); }
1863 ~ImGuiViewportP() { if (BgFgDrawLists[0]) IM_DELETE(BgFgDrawLists[0]); if (BgFgDrawLists[1]) IM_DELETE(BgFgDrawLists[1]); }
1864 void ClearRequestFlags() { PlatformRequestClose = PlatformRequestMove = PlatformRequestResize = false; }
1865
1866 // Calculate work rect pos/size given a set of offset (we have 1 pair of offset for rect locked from last frame data, and 1 pair for currently building rect)
1867 ImVec2 CalcWorkRectPos(const ImVec2& off_min) const { return ImVec2(Pos.x + off_min.x, Pos.y + off_min.y); }
1868 ImVec2 CalcWorkRectSize(const ImVec2& off_min, const ImVec2& off_max) const { return ImVec2(ImMax(0.0f, Size.x - off_min.x + off_max.x), ImMax(0.0f, Size.y - off_min.y + off_max.y)); }
1869 void UpdateWorkRect() { WorkPos = CalcWorkRectPos(WorkOffsetMin); WorkSize = CalcWorkRectSize(WorkOffsetMin, WorkOffsetMax); } // Update public fields
1870
1871 // Helpers to retrieve ImRect (we don't need to store BuildWorkRect as every access tend to change it, hence the code asymmetry)
1872 ImRect GetMainRect() const { return ImRect(Pos.x, Pos.y, Pos.x + Size.x, Pos.y + Size.y); }
1873 ImRect GetWorkRect() const { return ImRect(WorkPos.x, WorkPos.y, WorkPos.x + WorkSize.x, WorkPos.y + WorkSize.y); }
1874 ImRect GetBuildWorkRect() const { ImVec2 pos = CalcWorkRectPos(BuildWorkOffsetMin); ImVec2 size = CalcWorkRectSize(BuildWorkOffsetMin, BuildWorkOffsetMax); return ImRect(pos.x, pos.y, pos.x + size.x, pos.y + size.y); }
1875};

1879//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
1880
1881// Windows data saved in imgui.ini file
1882// Because we never destroy or rename ImGuiWindowSettings, we can store the names in a separate buffer easily.
1883// (this is designed to be stored in a ImChunkStream buffer, with the variable-length Name following our structure)
1884struct ImGuiWindowSettings
1885{
1886 ImGuiID ID;
1887 ImVec2ih Pos; // NB: Settings position are stored RELATIVE to the viewport! Whereas runtime ones are absolute positions.
1888 ImVec2ih Size;
1889 ImVec2ih ViewportPos;
1890 ImGuiID ViewportId;
1891 ImGuiID DockId; // ID of last known DockNode (even if the DockNode is invisible because it has only 1 active window), or 0 if none.
1892 ImGuiID ClassId; // ID of window class if specified
1893 short DockOrder; // Order of the last time the window was visible within its DockNode. This is used to reorder windows that are reappearing on the same frame. Same value between windows that were active and windows that were none are possible.
1894 bool Collapsed;
1895 bool IsChild;
1896 bool WantApply; // Set when loaded from .ini data (to enable merging/loading .ini data into an already running context)
1897 bool WantDelete; // Set to invalidate/delete the settings entry
1898
1899 ImGuiWindowSettings() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); DockOrder = -1; }
1900 char* GetName() { return (char*)(this + 1); }
1901};
1902
1903struct ImGuiSettingsHandler
1904{
1905 const char* TypeName; // Short description stored in .ini file. Disallowed characters: '[' ']'
1906 ImGuiID TypeHash; // == ImHashStr(TypeName)
1907 void (*ClearAllFn)(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiSettingsHandler* handler); // Clear all settings data
1908 void (*ReadInitFn)(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiSettingsHandler* handler); // Read: Called before reading (in registration order)
1909 void* (*ReadOpenFn)(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiSettingsHandler* handler, const char* name); // Read: Called when entering into a new ini entry e.g. "[Window][Name]"
1910 void (*ReadLineFn)(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiSettingsHandler* handler, void* entry, const char* line); // Read: Called for every line of text within an ini entry
1911 void (*ApplyAllFn)(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiSettingsHandler* handler); // Read: Called after reading (in registration order)
1912 void (*WriteAllFn)(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiSettingsHandler* handler, ImGuiTextBuffer* out_buf); // Write: Output every entries into 'out_buf'
1913 void* UserData;
1914
1915 ImGuiSettingsHandler() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); }
1916};

2035 ImGuiID Owner;
2036 ImGuiContextHookCallback Callback;
2037 void* UserData;
2038
2039 ImGuiContextHook() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); }
2040};

2560//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

2563
2564// Transient per-window data, reset at the beginning of the frame. This used to be called ImGuiDrawContext, hence the DC variable name in ImGuiWindow.
2565// (That's theory, in practice the delimitation between ImGuiWindow and ImGuiWindowTempData is quite tenuous and could be reconsidered..)
2566// (This doesn't need a constructor because we zero-clear it as part of ImGuiWindow and all frame-temporary data are setup on Begin)
2567struct IMGUI_API ImGuiWindowTempData
2568{
2569 // Layout
2570 ImVec2 CursorPos; // Current emitting position, in absolute coordinates.
2571 ImVec2 CursorPosPrevLine;
2572 ImVec2 CursorStartPos; // Initial position after Begin(), generally ~ window position + WindowPadding.
2573 ImVec2 CursorMaxPos; // Used to implicitly calculate ContentSize at the beginning of next frame, for scrolling range and auto-resize. Always growing during the frame.
2574 ImVec2 IdealMaxPos; // Used to implicitly calculate ContentSizeIdeal at the beginning of next frame, for auto-resize only. Always growing during the frame.
2575 ImVec2 CurrLineSize;
2576 ImVec2 PrevLineSize;
2577 float CurrLineTextBaseOffset; // Baseline offset (0.0f by default on a new line, generally == style.FramePadding.y when a framed item has been added).
2578 float PrevLineTextBaseOffset;
2579 bool IsSameLine;
2580 bool IsSetPos;
2581 ImVec1 Indent; // Indentation / start position from left of window (increased by TreePush/TreePop, etc.)
2582 ImVec1 ColumnsOffset; // Offset to the current column (if ColumnsCurrent > 0). FIXME: This and the above should be a stack to allow use cases like Tree->Column->Tree. Need revamp columns API.
2583 ImVec1 GroupOffset;
2584 ImVec2 CursorStartPosLossyness;// Record the loss of precision of CursorStartPos due to really large scrolling amount. This is used by clipper to compensate and fix the most common use case of large scroll area.
2585
2586 // Keyboard/Gamepad navigation
2587 ImGuiNavLayer NavLayerCurrent; // Current layer, 0..31 (we currently only use 0..1)
2588 short NavLayersActiveMask; // Which layers have been written to (result from previous frame)
2589 short NavLayersActiveMaskNext;// Which layers have been written to (accumulator for current frame)
2590 bool NavIsScrollPushableX; // Set when current work location may be scrolled horizontally when moving left / right. This is generally always true UNLESS within a column.
2591 bool NavHideHighlightOneFrame;
2592 bool NavWindowHasScrollY; // Set per window when scrolling can be used (== ScrollMax.y > 0.0f)
2593
2594 // Miscellaneous
2595 bool MenuBarAppending; // FIXME: Remove this
2596 ImVec2 MenuBarOffset; // MenuBarOffset.x is sort of equivalent of a per-layer CursorPos.x, saved/restored as we switch to the menu bar. The only situation when MenuBarOffset.y is > 0 if when (SafeAreaPadding.y > FramePadding.y), often used on TVs.
2597 ImGuiMenuColumns MenuColumns; // Simplified columns storage for menu items measurement
2598 int TreeDepth; // Current tree depth.
2599 ImU32 TreeJumpToParentOnPopMask; // Store a copy of !g.NavIdIsAlive for TreeDepth 0..31.. Could be turned into a ImU64 if necessary.
2600 ImVector<ImGuiWindow*> ChildWindows;
2601 ImGuiStorage* StateStorage; // Current persistent per-window storage (store e.g. tree node open/close state)
2602 ImGuiOldColumns* CurrentColumns; // Current columns set
2603 int CurrentTableIdx; // Current table index (into g.Tables)
2604 ImGuiLayoutType LayoutType;
2605 ImGuiLayoutType ParentLayoutType; // Layout type of parent window at the time of Begin()
2606
2607 // Local parameters stacks
2608 // We store the current settings outside of the vectors to increase memory locality (reduce cache misses). The vectors are rarely modified. Also it allows us to not heap allocate for short-lived windows which are not using those settings.
2609 float ItemWidth; // Current item width (>0.0: width in pixels, <0.0: align xx pixels to the right of window).
2610 float TextWrapPos; // Current text wrap pos.
2611 ImVector<float> ItemWidthStack; // Store item widths to restore (attention: .back() is not == ItemWidth)
2612 ImVector<float> TextWrapPosStack; // Store text wrap pos to restore (attention: .back() is not == TextWrapPos)
2613};

2615// Storage for one window
2616struct IMGUI_API ImGuiWindow
2617{
2618 ImGuiContext* Ctx; // Parent UI context (needs to be set explicitly by parent).
2619 char* Name; // Window name, owned by the window.
2620 ImGuiID ID; // == ImHashStr(Name)
2621 ImGuiWindowFlags Flags, FlagsPreviousFrame; // See enum ImGuiWindowFlags_
2622 ImGuiChildFlags ChildFlags; // Set when window is a child window. See enum ImGuiChildFlags_
2623 ImGuiWindowClass WindowClass; // Advanced users only. Set with SetNextWindowClass()
2624 ImGuiViewportP* Viewport; // Always set in Begin(). Inactive windows may have a NULL value here if their viewport was discarded.
2625 ImGuiID ViewportId; // We backup the viewport id (since the viewport may disappear or never be created if the window is inactive)
2626 ImVec2 ViewportPos; // We backup the viewport position (since the viewport may disappear or never be created if the window is inactive)
2627 int ViewportAllowPlatformMonitorExtend; // Reset to -1 every frame (index is guaranteed to be valid between NewFrame..EndFrame), only used in the Appearing frame of a tooltip/popup to enforce clamping to a given monitor
2628 ImVec2 Pos; // Position (always rounded-up to nearest pixel)
2629 ImVec2 Size; // Current size (==SizeFull or collapsed title bar size)
2630 ImVec2 SizeFull; // Size when non collapsed
2631 ImVec2 ContentSize; // Size of contents/scrollable client area (calculated from the extents reach of the cursor) from previous frame. Does not include window decoration or window padding.
2632 ImVec2 ContentSizeIdeal;
2633 ImVec2 ContentSizeExplicit; // Size of contents/scrollable client area explicitly request by the user via SetNextWindowContentSize().
2634 ImVec2 WindowPadding; // Window padding at the time of Begin().
2635 float WindowRounding; // Window rounding at the time of Begin(). May be clamped lower to avoid rendering artifacts with title bar, menu bar etc.
2636 float WindowBorderSize; // Window border size at the time of Begin().
2637 float DecoOuterSizeX1, DecoOuterSizeY1; // Left/Up offsets. Sum of non-scrolling outer decorations (X1 generally == 0.0f. Y1 generally = TitleBarHeight + MenuBarHeight). Locked during Begin().
2638 float DecoOuterSizeX2, DecoOuterSizeY2; // Right/Down offsets (X2 generally == ScrollbarSize.x, Y2 == ScrollbarSizes.y).
2639 float DecoInnerSizeX1, DecoInnerSizeY1; // Applied AFTER/OVER InnerRect. Specialized for Tables as they use specialized form of clipping and frozen rows/columns are inside InnerRect (and not part of regular decoration sizes).
2640 int NameBufLen; // Size of buffer storing Name. May be larger than strlen(Name)!
2641 ImGuiID MoveId; // == window->GetID("#MOVE")
2642 ImGuiID TabId; // == window->GetID("#TAB")
2643 ImGuiID ChildId; // ID of corresponding item in parent window (for navigation to return from child window to parent window)
2644 ImVec2 Scroll;
2645 ImVec2 ScrollMax;
2646 ImVec2 ScrollTarget; // target scroll position. stored as cursor position with scrolling canceled out, so the highest point is always 0.0f. (FLT_MAX for no change)
2647 ImVec2 ScrollTargetCenterRatio; // 0.0f = scroll so that target position is at top, 0.5f = scroll so that target position is centered
2648 ImVec2 ScrollTargetEdgeSnapDist; // 0.0f = no snapping, >0.0f snapping threshold
2649 ImVec2 ScrollbarSizes; // Size taken by each scrollbars on their smaller axis. Pay attention! ScrollbarSizes.x == width of the vertical scrollbar, ScrollbarSizes.y = height of the horizontal scrollbar.
2650 bool ScrollbarX, ScrollbarY; // Are scrollbars visible?
2651 bool ViewportOwned;
2652 bool Active; // Set to true on Begin(), unless Collapsed
2653 bool WasActive;
2654 bool WriteAccessed; // Set to true when any widget access the current window
2655 bool Collapsed; // Set when collapsing window to become only title-bar
2656 bool WantCollapseToggle;
2657 bool SkipItems; // Set when items can safely be all clipped (e.g. window not visible or collapsed)
2658 bool Appearing; // Set during the frame where the window is appearing (or re-appearing)
2659 bool Hidden; // Do not display (== HiddenFrames*** > 0)
2660 bool IsFallbackWindow; // Set on the "Debug##Default" window.
2661 bool IsExplicitChild; // Set when passed _ChildWindow, left to false by BeginDocked()
2662 bool HasCloseButton; // Set when the window has a close button (p_open != NULL)
2663 signed char ResizeBorderHovered; // Current border being hovered for resize (-1: none, otherwise 0-3)
2664 signed char ResizeBorderHeld; // Current border being held for resize (-1: none, otherwise 0-3)
2665 short BeginCount; // Number of Begin() during the current frame (generally 0 or 1, 1+ if appending via multiple Begin/End pairs)
2666 short BeginCountPreviousFrame; // Number of Begin() during the previous frame
2667 short BeginOrderWithinParent; // Begin() order within immediate parent window, if we are a child window. Otherwise 0.
2668 short BeginOrderWithinContext; // Begin() order within entire imgui context. This is mostly used for debugging submission order related issues.
2669 short FocusOrder; // Order within WindowsFocusOrder[], altered when windows are focused.
2670 ImGuiID PopupId; // ID in the popup stack when this window is used as a popup/menu (because we use generic Name/ID for recycling)
2671 ImS8 AutoFitFramesX, AutoFitFramesY;
2672 bool AutoFitOnlyGrows;
2673 ImGuiDir AutoPosLastDirection;
2674 ImS8 HiddenFramesCanSkipItems; // Hide the window for N frames
2675 ImS8 HiddenFramesCannotSkipItems; // Hide the window for N frames while allowing items to be submitted so we can measure their size
2676 ImS8 HiddenFramesForRenderOnly; // Hide the window until frame N at Render() time only
2677 ImS8 DisableInputsFrames; // Disable window interactions for N frames
2678 ImGuiCond SetWindowPosAllowFlags : 8; // store acceptable condition flags for SetNextWindowPos() use.
2679 ImGuiCond SetWindowSizeAllowFlags : 8; // store acceptable condition flags for SetNextWindowSize() use.
2680 ImGuiCond SetWindowCollapsedAllowFlags : 8; // store acceptable condition flags for SetNextWindowCollapsed() use.
2681 ImGuiCond SetWindowDockAllowFlags : 8; // store acceptable condition flags for SetNextWindowDock() use.
2682 ImVec2 SetWindowPosVal; // store window position when using a non-zero Pivot (position set needs to be processed when we know the window size)
2683 ImVec2 SetWindowPosPivot; // store window pivot for positioning. ImVec2(0, 0) when positioning from top-left corner; ImVec2(0.5f, 0.5f) for centering; ImVec2(1, 1) for bottom right.
2684
2685 ImVector<ImGuiID> IDStack; // ID stack. ID are hashes seeded with the value at the top of the stack. (In theory this should be in the TempData structure)
2686 ImGuiWindowTempData DC; // Temporary per-window data, reset at the beginning of the frame. This used to be called ImGuiDrawContext, hence the "DC" variable name.
2687
2688 // The best way to understand what those rectangles are is to use the 'Metrics->Tools->Show Windows Rectangles' viewer.
2689 // The main 'OuterRect', omitted as a field, is window->Rect().
2690 ImRect OuterRectClipped; // == Window->Rect() just after setup in Begin(). == window->Rect() for root window.
2691 ImRect InnerRect; // Inner rectangle (omit title bar, menu bar, scroll bar)
2692 ImRect InnerClipRect; // == InnerRect shrunk by WindowPadding*0.5f on each side, clipped within viewport or parent clip rect.
2693 ImRect WorkRect; // Initially covers the whole scrolling region. Reduced by containers e.g columns/tables when active. Shrunk by WindowPadding*1.0f on each side. This is meant to replace ContentRegionRect over time (from 1.71+ onward).
2694 ImRect ParentWorkRect; // Backup of WorkRect before entering a container such as columns/tables. Used by e.g. SpanAllColumns functions to easily access. Stacked containers are responsible for maintaining this. // FIXME-WORKRECT: Could be a stack?
2695 ImRect ClipRect; // Current clipping/scissoring rectangle, evolve as we are using PushClipRect(), etc. == DrawList->clip_rect_stack.back().
2696 ImRect ContentRegionRect; // FIXME: This is currently confusing/misleading. It is essentially WorkRect but not handling of scrolling. We currently rely on it as right/bottom aligned sizing operation need some size to rely on.
2697 ImVec2ih HitTestHoleSize; // Define an optional rectangular hole where mouse will pass-through the window.
2698 ImVec2ih HitTestHoleOffset;
2699
2700 int LastFrameActive; // Last frame number the window was Active.
2701 int LastFrameJustFocused; // Last frame number the window was made Focused.
2702 float LastTimeActive; // Last timestamp the window was Active (using float as we don't need high precision there)
2703 float ItemWidthDefault;
2704 ImGuiStorage StateStorage;
2705 ImVector<ImGuiOldColumns> ColumnsStorage;
2706 float FontWindowScale; // User scale multiplier per-window, via SetWindowFontScale()
2707 float FontDpiScale;
2708 int SettingsOffset; // Offset into SettingsWindows[] (offsets are always valid as we only grow the array from the back)
2709
2710 ImDrawList* DrawList; // == &DrawListInst (for backward compatibility reason with code using imgui_internal.h we keep this a pointer)
2711 ImDrawList DrawListInst;
2712 ImGuiWindow* ParentWindow; // If we are a child _or_ popup _or_ docked window, this is pointing to our parent. Otherwise NULL.
2713 ImGuiWindow* ParentWindowInBeginStack;
2714 ImGuiWindow* RootWindow; // Point to ourself or first ancestor that is not a child window. Doesn't cross through popups/dock nodes.
2715 ImGuiWindow* RootWindowPopupTree; // Point to ourself or first ancestor that is not a child window. Cross through popups parent<>child.
2716 ImGuiWindow* RootWindowDockTree; // Point to ourself or first ancestor that is not a child window. Cross through dock nodes.
2717 ImGuiWindow* RootWindowForTitleBarHighlight; // Point to ourself or first ancestor which will display TitleBgActive color when this window is active.
2718 ImGuiWindow* RootWindowForNav; // Point to ourself or first ancestor which doesn't have the NavFlattened flag.
2719
2720 ImGuiWindow* NavLastChildNavWindow; // When going to the menu bar, we remember the child window we came from. (This could probably be made implicit if we kept g.Windows sorted by last focused including child window.)
2721 ImGuiID NavLastIds[ImGuiNavLayer_COUNT]; // Last known NavId for this window, per layer (0/1)
2722 ImRect NavRectRel[ImGuiNavLayer_COUNT]; // Reference rectangle, in window relative space
2723 ImVec2 NavPreferredScoringPosRel[ImGuiNavLayer_COUNT]; // Preferred X/Y position updated when moving on a given axis, reset to FLT_MAX.
2724 ImGuiID NavRootFocusScopeId; // Focus Scope ID at the time of Begin()
2725
2726 int MemoryDrawListIdxCapacity; // Backup of last idx/vtx count, so when waking up the window we can preallocate and avoid iterative alloc/copy
2727 int MemoryDrawListVtxCapacity;
2728 bool MemoryCompacted; // Set when window extraneous data have been garbage collected
2729
2730 // Docking
2731 bool DockIsActive :1; // When docking artifacts are actually visible. When this is set, DockNode is guaranteed to be != NULL. ~~ (DockNode != NULL) && (DockNode->Windows.Size > 1).
2732 bool DockNodeIsVisible :1;
2733 bool DockTabIsVisible :1; // Is our window visible this frame? ~~ is the corresponding tab selected?
2734 bool DockTabWantClose :1;
2735 short DockOrder; // Order of the last time the window was visible within its DockNode. This is used to reorder windows that are reappearing on the same frame. Same value between windows that were active and windows that were none are possible.
2736 ImGuiWindowDockStyle DockStyle;
2737 ImGuiDockNode* DockNode; // Which node are we docked into. Important: Prefer testing DockIsActive in many cases as this will still be set when the dock node is hidden.
2738 ImGuiDockNode* DockNodeAsHost; // Which node are we owning (for parent windows)
2739 ImGuiID DockId; // Backup of last valid DockNode->ID, so single window remember their dock node id even when they are not bound any more
2740 ImGuiItemStatusFlags DockTabItemStatusFlags;
2741 ImRect DockTabItemRect;
2742
2743public:
2744 ImGuiWindow(ImGuiContext* context, const char* name);
2745 ~ImGuiWindow();
2746
2747 ImGuiID GetID(const char* str, const char* str_end = NULL);
2748 ImGuiID GetID(const void* ptr);
2749 ImGuiID GetID(int n);
2750 ImGuiID GetIDFromRectangle(const ImRect& r_abs);
2751
2752 // We don't use g.FontSize because the window may be != g.CurrentWindow.
2753 ImRect Rect() const { return ImRect(Pos.x, Pos.y, Pos.x + Size.x, Pos.y + Size.y); }
2754 float CalcFontSize() const { ImGuiContext& g = *Ctx; float scale = g.FontBaseSize * FontWindowScale * FontDpiScale; if (ParentWindow) scale *= ParentWindow->FontWindowScale; return scale; }
2755 float TitleBarHeight() const { ImGuiContext& g = *Ctx; return (Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_NoTitleBar) ? 0.0f : CalcFontSize() + g.Style.FramePadding.y * 2.0f; }
2756 ImRect TitleBarRect() const { return ImRect(Pos, ImVec2(Pos.x + SizeFull.x, Pos.y + TitleBarHeight())); }
2757 float MenuBarHeight() const { ImGuiContext& g = *Ctx; return (Flags & ImGuiWindowFlags_MenuBar) ? DC.MenuBarOffset.y + CalcFontSize() + g.Style.FramePadding.y * 2.0f : 0.0f; }
2758 ImRect MenuBarRect() const { float y1 = Pos.y + TitleBarHeight(); return ImRect(Pos.x, y1, Pos.x + SizeFull.x, y1 + MenuBarHeight()); }
2759};

2775{
2776 ImGuiTabItemFlags_SectionMask_ = ImGuiTabItemFlags_Leading | ImGuiTabItemFlags_Trailing,
2777 ImGuiTabItemFlags_NoCloseButton = 1 << 20, // Track whether p_open was set or not (we'll need this info on the next frame to recompute ContentWidth during layout)
2778 ImGuiTabItemFlags_Button = 1 << 21, // Used by TabItemButton, change the tab item behavior to mimic a button
2779 ImGuiTabItemFlags_Unsorted = 1 << 22, // [Docking] Trailing tabs with the _Unsorted flag will be sorted based on the DockOrder of their Window.
2780};

2782// Storage for one active tab item (sizeof() 48 bytes)
2783struct ImGuiTabItem
2784{

2792 float ContentWidth; // Width of label, stored during BeginTabItem() call
2793 float RequestedWidth; // Width optionally requested by caller, -1.0f is unused
2794 ImS32 NameOffset; // When Window==NULL, offset to name within parent ImGuiTabBar::TabsNames
2795 ImS16 BeginOrder; // BeginTabItem() order, used to re-order tabs after toggling ImGuiTabBarFlags_Reorderable
2796 ImS16 IndexDuringLayout; // Index only used during TabBarLayout(). Tabs gets reordered so 'Tabs[n].IndexDuringLayout == n' but may mismatch during additions.
2797 bool WantClose; // Marked as closed by SetTabItemClosed()
2798
2799 ImGuiTabItem() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); LastFrameVisible = LastFrameSelected = -1; RequestedWidth = -1.0f; NameOffset = -1; BeginOrder = IndexDuringLayout = -1; }
2800};
