2842//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2843// [SECTION] Table support
2844//-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
2845
2846#define IM_COL32_DISABLE IM_COL32(0,0,0,1) // Special sentinel code which cannot be used as a regular color.
2847#define IMGUI_TABLE_MAX_COLUMNS 512 // May be further lifted
2848
2849// Our current column maximum is 64 but we may raise that in the future.
2850typedef ImS16 ImGuiTableColumnIdx;
2851typedef ImU16 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx;
2852
2853// [Internal] sizeof() ~ 112
2854// We use the terminology "Enabled" to refer to a column that is not Hidden by user/api.
2855// We use the terminology "Clipped" to refer to a column that is out of sight because of scrolling/clipping.
2856// This is in contrast with some user-facing api such as IsItemVisible() / IsRectVisible() which use "Visible" to mean "not clipped".
2857struct ImGuiTableColumn
2858{
2859 ImGuiTableColumnFlags Flags; // Flags after some patching (not directly same as provided by user). See ImGuiTableColumnFlags_
2860 float WidthGiven; // Final/actual width visible == (MaxX - MinX), locked in TableUpdateLayout(). May be > WidthRequest to honor minimum width, may be < WidthRequest to honor shrinking columns down in tight space.
2861 float MinX; // Absolute positions
2862 float MaxX;
2863 float WidthRequest; // Master width absolute value when !(Flags & _WidthStretch). When Stretch this is derived every frame from StretchWeight in TableUpdateLayout()
2864 float WidthAuto; // Automatic width
2865 float StretchWeight; // Master width weight when (Flags & _WidthStretch). Often around ~1.0f initially.
2866 float InitStretchWeightOrWidth; // Value passed to TableSetupColumn(). For Width it is a content width (_without padding_).
2867 ImRect ClipRect; // Clipping rectangle for the column
2868 ImGuiID UserID; // Optional, value passed to TableSetupColumn()
2869 float WorkMinX; // Contents region min ~(MinX + CellPaddingX + CellSpacingX1) == cursor start position when entering column
2870 float WorkMaxX; // Contents region max ~(MaxX - CellPaddingX - CellSpacingX2)
2871 float ItemWidth; // Current item width for the column, preserved across rows
2872 float ContentMaxXFrozen; // Contents maximum position for frozen rows (apart from headers), from which we can infer content width.
2873 float ContentMaxXUnfrozen;
2874 float ContentMaxXHeadersUsed; // Contents maximum position for headers rows (regardless of freezing). TableHeader() automatically softclip itself + report ideal desired size, to avoid creating extraneous draw calls
2875 float ContentMaxXHeadersIdeal;
2876 ImS16 NameOffset; // Offset into parent ColumnsNames[]
2877 ImGuiTableColumnIdx DisplayOrder; // Index within Table's IndexToDisplayOrder[] (column may be reordered by users)
2878 ImGuiTableColumnIdx IndexWithinEnabledSet; // Index within enabled/visible set (<= IndexToDisplayOrder)
2879 ImGuiTableColumnIdx PrevEnabledColumn; // Index of prev enabled/visible column within Columns[], -1 if first enabled/visible column
2880 ImGuiTableColumnIdx NextEnabledColumn; // Index of next enabled/visible column within Columns[], -1 if last enabled/visible column
2881 ImGuiTableColumnIdx SortOrder; // Index of this column within sort specs, -1 if not sorting on this column, 0 for single-sort, may be >0 on multi-sort
2882 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx DrawChannelCurrent; // Index within DrawSplitter.Channels[]
2883 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx DrawChannelFrozen; // Draw channels for frozen rows (often headers)
2884 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx DrawChannelUnfrozen; // Draw channels for unfrozen rows
2885 bool IsEnabled; // IsUserEnabled && (Flags & ImGuiTableColumnFlags_Disabled) == 0
2886 bool IsUserEnabled; // Is the column not marked Hidden by the user? (unrelated to being off view, e.g. clipped by scrolling).
2887 bool IsUserEnabledNextFrame;
2888 bool IsVisibleX; // Is actually in view (e.g. overlapping the host window clipping rectangle, not scrolled).
2889 bool IsVisibleY;
2890 bool IsRequestOutput; // Return value for TableSetColumnIndex() / TableNextColumn(): whether we request user to output contents or not.
2891 bool IsSkipItems; // Do we want item submissions to this column to be completely ignored (no layout will happen).
2892 bool IsPreserveWidthAuto;
2893 ImS8 NavLayerCurrent; // ImGuiNavLayer in 1 byte
2894 ImU8 AutoFitQueue; // Queue of 8 values for the next 8 frames to request auto-fit
2895 ImU8 CannotSkipItemsQueue; // Queue of 8 values for the next 8 frames to disable Clipped/SkipItem
2896 ImU8 SortDirection : 2; // ImGuiSortDirection_Ascending or ImGuiSortDirection_Descending
2897 ImU8 SortDirectionsAvailCount : 2; // Number of available sort directions (0 to 3)
2898 ImU8 SortDirectionsAvailMask : 4; // Mask of available sort directions (1-bit each)
2899 ImU8 SortDirectionsAvailList; // Ordered list of available sort directions (2-bits each, total 8-bits)
2900
2901 ImGuiTableColumn()
2902 {

2937// sizeof() ~ 580 bytes + heap allocs described in TableBeginInitMemory()
2938struct IMGUI_API ImGuiTable
2939{

2941 ImGuiTableFlags Flags;
2942 void* RawData; // Single allocation to hold Columns[], DisplayOrderToIndex[] and RowCellData[]

2944 ImSpan<ImGuiTableColumn> Columns; // Point within RawData[]

2946 ImSpan<ImGuiTableCellData> RowCellData; // Point within RawData[]. Store cells background requests for current row.
2947 ImBitArrayPtr EnabledMaskByDisplayOrder; // Column DisplayOrder -> IsEnabled map
2948 ImBitArrayPtr EnabledMaskByIndex; // Column Index -> IsEnabled map (== not hidden by user/api) in a format adequate for iterating column without touching cold data

2954 int CurrentRow;
2955 int CurrentColumn;
2956 ImS16 InstanceCurrent; // Count of BeginTable() calls with same ID in the same frame (generally 0). This is a little bit similar to BeginCount for a window, but multiple table with same ID look are multiple tables, they are just synched.
2957 ImS16 InstanceInteracted; // Mark which instance (generally 0) of the same ID is being interacted with
2958 float RowPosY1;
2959 float RowPosY2;

2961 float RowCellPaddingY; // Top and bottom padding. Reloaded during row change.

2965 ImGuiTableRowFlags LastRowFlags : 16;

2967 ImU32 RowBgColor[2]; // Background color override for current row.
2968 ImU32 BorderColorStrong;
2969 ImU32 BorderColorLight;
2970 float BorderX1;

2973 float MinColumnWidth;
2974 float OuterPaddingX;

2976 float CellSpacingX1; // Spacing between non-bordered cells. Locked in BeginTable()/Layout.
2977 float CellSpacingX2;
2978 float InnerWidth; // User value passed to BeginTable(), see comments at the top of BeginTable() for details.
2979 float ColumnsGivenWidth; // Sum of current column width
2980 float ColumnsAutoFitWidth; // Sum of ideal column width in order nothing to be clipped, used for auto-fitting and content width submission in outer window
2981 float ColumnsStretchSumWeights; // Sum of weight of all enabled stretching columns
2982 float ResizedColumnNextWidth;
2983 float ResizeLockMinContentsX2; // Lock minimum contents width while resizing down in order to not create feedback loops. But we allow growing the table.
2984 float RefScale; // Reference scale to be able to rescale columns on font/dpi changes.
2985 float AngledHeadersHeight; // Set by TableAngledHeadersRow(), used in TableUpdateLayout()
2986 float AngledHeadersSlope; // Set by TableAngledHeadersRow(), used in TableUpdateLayout()
2987 ImRect OuterRect; // Note: for non-scrolling table, OuterRect.Max.y is often FLT_MAX until EndTable(), unless a height has been specified in BeginTable().
2988 ImRect InnerRect; // InnerRect but without decoration. As with OuterRect, for non-scrolling tables, InnerRect.Max.y is
2989 ImRect WorkRect;
2990 ImRect InnerClipRect;
2991 ImRect BgClipRect; // We use this to cpu-clip cell background color fill, evolve during the frame as we cross frozen rows boundaries
2992 ImRect Bg0ClipRectForDrawCmd; // Actual ImDrawCmd clip rect for BG0/1 channel. This tends to be == OuterWindow->ClipRect at BeginTable() because output in BG0/BG1 is cpu-clipped
2993 ImRect Bg2ClipRectForDrawCmd; // Actual ImDrawCmd clip rect for BG2 channel. This tends to be a correct, tight-fit, because output to BG2 are done by widgets relying on regular ClipRect.
2994 ImRect HostClipRect; // This is used to check if we can eventually merge our columns draw calls into the current draw call of the current window.
2995 ImRect HostBackupInnerClipRect; // Backup of InnerWindow->ClipRect during PushTableBackground()/PopTableBackground()
2996 ImGuiWindow* OuterWindow; // Parent window for the table
2997 ImGuiWindow* InnerWindow; // Window holding the table data (== OuterWindow or a child window)
2998 ImGuiTextBuffer ColumnsNames; // Contiguous buffer holding columns names
2999 ImDrawListSplitter* DrawSplitter; // Shortcut to TempData->DrawSplitter while in table. Isolate draw commands per columns to avoid switching clip rect constantly
3000 ImGuiTableInstanceData InstanceDataFirst;
3001 ImVector<ImGuiTableInstanceData> InstanceDataExtra; // FIXME-OPT: Using a small-vector pattern would be good.
3002 ImGuiTableColumnSortSpecs SortSpecsSingle;
3003 ImVector<ImGuiTableColumnSortSpecs> SortSpecsMulti; // FIXME-OPT: Using a small-vector pattern would be good.
3004 ImGuiTableSortSpecs SortSpecs; // Public facing sorts specs, this is what we return in TableGetSortSpecs()
3005 ImGuiTableColumnIdx SortSpecsCount;
3006 ImGuiTableColumnIdx ColumnsEnabledCount; // Number of enabled columns (<= ColumnsCount)
3007 ImGuiTableColumnIdx ColumnsEnabledFixedCount; // Number of enabled columns (<= ColumnsCount)
3008 ImGuiTableColumnIdx DeclColumnsCount; // Count calls to TableSetupColumn()
3009 ImGuiTableColumnIdx AngledHeadersCount; // Count columns with angled headers
3010 ImGuiTableColumnIdx HoveredColumnBody; // Index of column whose visible region is being hovered. Important: == ColumnsCount when hovering empty region after the right-most column!
3011 ImGuiTableColumnIdx HoveredColumnBorder; // Index of column whose right-border is being hovered (for resizing).
3012 ImGuiTableColumnIdx HighlightColumnHeader; // Index of column which should be highlighted.
3013 ImGuiTableColumnIdx AutoFitSingleColumn; // Index of single column requesting auto-fit.
3014 ImGuiTableColumnIdx ResizedColumn; // Index of column being resized. Reset when InstanceCurrent==0.

3020 ImGuiTableColumnIdx RightMostEnabledColumn; // Index of right-most non-hidden column.

3031 ImGuiTableDrawChannelIdx Bg2DrawChannelUnfrozen;

3033 bool IsInsideRow; // Set when inside TableBeginRow()/TableEndRow().
3034 bool IsInitializing;
3035 bool IsSortSpecsDirty;
3036 bool IsUsingHeaders; // Set when the first row had the ImGuiTableRowFlags_Headers flag.
3037 bool IsContextPopupOpen; // Set when default context menu is open (also see: ContextPopupColumn, InstanceInteracted).

3039 bool IsSettingsRequestLoad;

3057// Transient data that are only needed between BeginTable() and EndTable(), those buffers are shared (1 per level of stacked table).
3058// - Accessing those requires chasing an extra pointer so for very frequently used data we leave them in the main table structure.
3059// - We also leave out of this structure data that tend to be particularly useful for debugging/metrics.
3060// sizeof() ~ 120 bytes.

3065 float AngledheadersExtraWidth; // Used in EndTable()
3066
3067 ImVec2 UserOuterSize; // outer_size.x passed to BeginTable()
3068 ImDrawListSplitter DrawSplitter;
3069
3070 ImRect HostBackupWorkRect; // Backup of InnerWindow->WorkRect at the end of BeginTable()
3071 ImRect HostBackupParentWorkRect; // Backup of InnerWindow->ParentWorkRect at the end of BeginTable()
3072 ImVec2 HostBackupPrevLineSize; // Backup of InnerWindow->DC.PrevLineSize at the end of BeginTable()
3073 ImVec2 HostBackupCurrLineSize; // Backup of InnerWindow->DC.CurrLineSize at the end of BeginTable()
3074 ImVec2 HostBackupCursorMaxPos; // Backup of InnerWindow->DC.CursorMaxPos at the end of BeginTable()
3075 ImVec1 HostBackupColumnsOffset; // Backup of OuterWindow->DC.ColumnsOffset at the end of BeginTable()
3076 float HostBackupItemWidth; // Backup of OuterWindow->DC.ItemWidth at the end of BeginTable()
3077 int HostBackupItemWidthStackSize;//Backup of OuterWindow->DC.ItemWidthStack.Size at the end of BeginTable()
3078
3079 ImGuiTableTempData() { memset(this, 0, sizeof(*this)); LastTimeActive = -1.0f; }
3080};

3318 // FIXME: Eventually we should aim to move e.g. IsActiveIdUsingKey() into IsKeyXXX functions.
3319 inline bool IsNamedKey(ImGuiKey key) { return key >= ImGuiKey_NamedKey_BEGIN && key < ImGuiKey_NamedKey_END; }
3320 inline bool IsNamedKeyOrModKey(ImGuiKey key) { return (key >= ImGuiKey_NamedKey_BEGIN && key < ImGuiKey_NamedKey_END) || key == ImGuiMod_Ctrl || key == ImGuiMod_Shift || key == ImGuiMod_Alt || key == ImGuiMod_Super || key == ImGuiMod_Shortcut; }
3321 inline bool IsLegacyKey(ImGuiKey key) { return key >= ImGuiKey_LegacyNativeKey_BEGIN && key < ImGuiKey_LegacyNativeKey_END; }
3322 inline bool IsKeyboardKey(ImGuiKey key) { return key >= ImGuiKey_Keyboard_BEGIN && key < ImGuiKey_Keyboard_END; }
3323 inline bool IsGamepadKey(ImGuiKey key) { return key >= ImGuiKey_Gamepad_BEGIN && key < ImGuiKey_Gamepad_END; }
3324 inline bool IsMouseKey(ImGuiKey key) { return key >= ImGuiKey_Mouse_BEGIN && key < ImGuiKey_Mouse_END; }
3325 inline bool IsAliasKey(ImGuiKey key) { return key >= ImGuiKey_Aliases_BEGIN && key < ImGuiKey_Aliases_END; }
3326 inline ImGuiKeyChord ConvertShortcutMod(ImGuiKeyChord key_chord) { ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui; IM_ASSERT_PARANOID(key_chord & ImGuiMod_Shortcut); return (key_chord & ~ImGuiMod_Shortcut) | (g.IO.ConfigMacOSXBehaviors ? ImGuiMod_Super : ImGuiMod_Ctrl); }
3327 inline ImGuiKey ConvertSingleModFlagToKey(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiKey key)
3328 {
3329 ImGuiContext& g = *ctx;
3330 if (key == ImGuiMod_Ctrl) return ImGuiKey_ReservedForModCtrl;
3331 if (key == ImGuiMod_Shift) return ImGuiKey_ReservedForModShift;
3332 if (key == ImGuiMod_Alt) return ImGuiKey_ReservedForModAlt;
3333 if (key == ImGuiMod_Super) return ImGuiKey_ReservedForModSuper;
3334 if (key == ImGuiMod_Shortcut) return (g.IO.ConfigMacOSXBehaviors ? ImGuiKey_ReservedForModSuper : ImGuiKey_ReservedForModCtrl);
3335 return key;
3336 }

3351 // [EXPERIMENTAL] Low-Level: Key/Input Ownership
3352 // - The idea is that instead of "eating" a given input, we can link to an owner id.
3353 // - Ownership is most often claimed as a result of reacting to a press/down event (but occasionally may be claimed ahead).
3354 // - Input queries can then read input by specifying ImGuiKeyOwner_Any (== 0), ImGuiKeyOwner_None (== -1) or a custom ID.
3355 // - Legacy input queries (without specifying an owner or _Any or _None) are equivalent to using ImGuiKeyOwner_Any (== 0).
3356 // - Input ownership is automatically released on the frame after a key is released. Therefore:
3357 // - for ownership registration happening as a result of a down/press event, the SetKeyOwner() call may be done once (common case).
3358 // - for ownership registration happening ahead of a down/press event, the SetKeyOwner() call needs to be made every frame (happens if e.g. claiming ownership on hover).
3359 // - SetItemKeyOwner() is a shortcut for common simple case. A custom widget will probably want to call SetKeyOwner() multiple times directly based on its interaction state.
3360 // - This is marked experimental because not all widgets are fully honoring the Set/Test idioms. We will need to move forward step by step.
3361 // Please open a GitHub Issue to submit your usage scenario or if there's a use case you need solved.
3362 IMGUI_API ImGuiID GetKeyOwner(ImGuiKey key);
3363 IMGUI_API void SetKeyOwner(ImGuiKey key, ImGuiID owner_id, ImGuiInputFlags flags = 0);
3364 IMGUI_API void SetKeyOwnersForKeyChord(ImGuiKeyChord key, ImGuiID owner_id, ImGuiInputFlags flags = 0);
3365 IMGUI_API void SetItemKeyOwner(ImGuiKey key, ImGuiInputFlags flags = 0); // Set key owner to last item if it is hovered or active. Equivalent to 'if (IsItemHovered() || IsItemActive()) { SetKeyOwner(key, GetItemID());'.
3366 IMGUI_API bool TestKeyOwner(ImGuiKey key, ImGuiID owner_id); // Test that key is either not owned, either owned by 'owner_id'
3367 inline ImGuiKeyOwnerData* GetKeyOwnerData(ImGuiContext* ctx, ImGuiKey key) { if (key & ImGuiMod_Mask_) key = ConvertSingleModFlagToKey(ctx, key); IM_ASSERT(IsNamedKey(key)); return &ctx->KeysOwnerData[key - ImGuiKey_NamedKey_BEGIN]; }
3368
3369 // [EXPERIMENTAL] High-Level: Input Access functions w/ support for Key/Input Ownership
3370 // - Important: legacy IsKeyPressed(ImGuiKey, bool repeat=true) _DEFAULTS_ to repeat, new IsKeyPressed() requires _EXPLICIT_ ImGuiInputFlags_Repeat flag.
3371 // - Expected to be later promoted to public API, the prototypes are designed to replace existing ones (since owner_id can default to Any == 0)
3372 // - Specifying a value for 'ImGuiID owner' will test that EITHER the key is NOT owned (UNLESS locked), EITHER the key is owned by 'owner'.
3373 // Legacy functions use ImGuiKeyOwner_Any meaning that they typically ignore ownership, unless a call to SetKeyOwner() explicitly used ImGuiInputFlags_LockThisFrame or ImGuiInputFlags_LockUntilRelease.
3374 // - Binding generators may want to ignore those for now, or suffix them with Ex() until we decide if this gets moved into public API.
3375 IMGUI_API bool IsKeyDown(ImGuiKey key, ImGuiID owner_id);
3376 IMGUI_API bool IsKeyPressed(ImGuiKey key, ImGuiID owner_id, ImGuiInputFlags flags = 0); // Important: when transitioning from old to new IsKeyPressed(): old API has "bool repeat = true", so would default to repeat. New API requiress explicit ImGuiInputFlags_Repeat.
3377 IMGUI_API bool IsKeyReleased(ImGuiKey key, ImGuiID owner_id);
3378 IMGUI_API bool IsMouseDown(ImGuiMouseButton button, ImGuiID owner_id);
3379 IMGUI_API bool IsMouseClicked(ImGuiMouseButton button, ImGuiID owner_id, ImGuiInputFlags flags = 0);
3380 IMGUI_API bool IsMouseReleased(ImGuiMouseButton button, ImGuiID owner_id);
3381 IMGUI_API bool IsMouseDoubleClicked(ImGuiMouseButton button, ImGuiID owner_id);

3383 // [EXPERIMENTAL] Shortcut Routing
3384 // - ImGuiKeyChord = a ImGuiKey optionally OR-red with ImGuiMod_Alt/ImGuiMod_Ctrl/ImGuiMod_Shift/ImGuiMod_Super.
3385 // ImGuiKey_C (accepted by functions taking ImGuiKey or ImGuiKeyChord)
3386 // ImGuiKey_C | ImGuiMod_Ctrl (accepted by functions taking ImGuiKeyChord)
3387 // ONLY ImGuiMod_XXX values are legal to 'OR' with an ImGuiKey. You CANNOT 'OR' two ImGuiKey values.
3388 // - When using one of the routing flags (e.g. ImGuiInputFlags_RouteFocused): routes requested ahead of time given a chord (key + modifiers) and a routing policy.
3389 // - Routes are resolved during NewFrame(): if keyboard modifiers are matching current ones: SetKeyOwner() is called + route is granted for the frame.
3390 // - Route is granted to a single owner. When multiple requests are made we have policies to select the winning route.
3391 // - Multiple read sites may use the same owner id and will all get the granted route.
3392 // - For routing: when owner_id is 0 we use the current Focus Scope ID as a default owner in order to identify our location.
3393 // - TL;DR;
3394 // - IsKeyChordPressed() compares mods + call IsKeyPressed() -> function has no side-effect.
3395 // - Shortcut() submits a route then if currently can be routed calls IsKeyChordPressed() -> function has (desirable) side-effects.
3396 IMGUI_API bool IsKeyChordPressed(ImGuiKeyChord key_chord, ImGuiID owner_id, ImGuiInputFlags flags = 0);
3397 IMGUI_API bool Shortcut(ImGuiKeyChord key_chord, ImGuiID owner_id = 0, ImGuiInputFlags flags = 0);
3398 IMGUI_API bool SetShortcutRouting(ImGuiKeyChord key_chord, ImGuiID owner_id = 0, ImGuiInputFlags flags = 0);
3399 IMGUI_API bool TestShortcutRouting(ImGuiKeyChord key_chord, ImGuiID owner_id);
3400 IMGUI_API ImGuiKeyRoutingData* GetShortcutRoutingData(ImGuiKeyChord key_chord);

3433 // Docking - Builder function needs to be generally called before the node is used/submitted.
3434 // - The DockBuilderXXX functions are designed to _eventually_ become a public API, but it is too early to expose it and guarantee stability.
3435 // - Do not hold on ImGuiDockNode* pointers! They may be invalidated by any split/merge/remove operation and every frame.
3436 // - To create a DockSpace() node, make sure to set the ImGuiDockNodeFlags_DockSpace flag when calling DockBuilderAddNode().
3437 // You can create dockspace nodes (attached to a window) _or_ floating nodes (carry its own window) with this API.
3438 // - DockBuilderSplitNode() create 2 child nodes within 1 node. The initial node becomes a parent node.
3439 // - If you intend to split the node immediately after creation using DockBuilderSplitNode(), make sure
3440 // to call DockBuilderSetNodeSize() beforehand. If you don't, the resulting split sizes may not be reliable.
3441 // - Call DockBuilderFinish() after you are done.

3457 // [EXPERIMENTAL] Focus Scope
3458 // This is generally used to identify a unique input location (for e.g. a selection set)
3459 // There is one per window (automatically set in Begin), but:
3460 // - Selection patterns generally need to react (e.g. clear a selection) when landing on one item of the set.
3461 // So in order to identify a set multiple lists in same window may each need a focus scope.
3462 // If you imagine an hypothetical BeginSelectionGroup()/EndSelectionGroup() api, it would likely call PushFocusScope()/EndFocusScope()
3463 // - Shortcut routing also use focus scope as a default location identifier if an owner is not provided.
3464 // We don't use the ID Stack for this as it is common to want them separate.
3465 IMGUI_API void PushFocusScope(ImGuiID id);
3466 IMGUI_API void PopFocusScope();
3467 inline ImGuiID GetCurrentFocusScope() { ImGuiContext& g = *GImGui; return g.CurrentFocusScopeId; } // Focus scope we are outputting into, set by PushFocusScope()

3716 // Refactored focus/nav/tabbing system in 1.82 and 1.84. If you have old/custom copy-and-pasted widgets that used FocusableItemRegister():
3717 // (Old) IMGUI_VERSION_NUM < 18209: using 'ItemAdd(....)' and 'bool tab_focused = FocusableItemRegister(...)'
3718 // (Old) IMGUI_VERSION_NUM >= 18209: using 'ItemAdd(..., ImGuiItemAddFlags_Focusable)' and 'bool tab_focused = (GetItemStatusFlags() & ImGuiItemStatusFlags_Focused) != 0'
3719 // (New) IMGUI_VERSION_NUM >= 18413: using 'ItemAdd(..., ImGuiItemFlags_Inputable)' and 'bool tab_focused = (GetItemStatusFlags() & ImGuiItemStatusFlags_FocusedTabbing) != 0 || (g.NavActivateId == id && (g.NavActivateFlags & ImGuiActivateFlags_PreferInput))' (WIP)
3720 // Widget code are simplified as there's no need to call FocusableItemUnregister() while managing the transition from regular widget to TempInputText()
3721 inline bool FocusableItemRegister(ImGuiWindow* window, ImGuiID id) { IM_ASSERT(0); IM_UNUSED(window); IM_UNUSED(id); return false; } // -> pass ImGuiItemAddFlags_Inputable flag to ItemAdd()
3722 inline void FocusableItemUnregister(ImGuiWindow* window) { IM_ASSERT(0); IM_UNUSED(window); } // -> unnecessary: TempInputText() uses ImGuiInputTextFlags_MergedItem
3723#endif

3726#endif
